<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="sp1_001"></A>Reading
this Prospectus</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">This prospectus contains information about Ford
Credit Floorplan Master Owner Trust A and the terms of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes to be issued by the trust. You should only rely
on information in or referenced in this prospectus and any information incorporated by reference into the registration statement for
this securitization transaction filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission, or &quot;SEC,&quot; that includes this prospectus.
Ford Credit has not authorized anyone to provide you with different information.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">This prospectus starts with the following brief
introductory sections:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Transaction
                                            Diagrams</I> &mdash; separate diagrams show the structure of this securitization transaction,
                                            the credit enhancement available for the notes, transaction payments and the role of each
                                            transaction party and transaction document in this securitization transaction,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Summary
                                            </I>&mdash; provides an overview of the series, the assets of the trust, the cash flows of
                                            the series and the credit enhancement available for the series, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Risk
                                            Factors</I> &mdash; describes the material risks of investing in the notes.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The other sections of this prospectus contain
more details about the series and the structure of the series. Cross-references refer you to more details about a particular topic or
related information elsewhere in this prospectus. The Table of Contents contains references to key topics.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">An index of defined terms is at the end of this
prospectus.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="sp1_002"></A>Forward-Looking
Statements</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Any projections, expectations and estimates in
this prospectus are not historical in nature but are forward-looking statements based on information and assumptions Ford Credit and
the depositors consider reasonable. Forward-looking statements are about circumstances and events that have not yet taken place, so they
are uncertain and may vary materially from actual events. Neither Ford Credit nor either depositor is obligated to update or revise any
forward-looking statements, including changes in economic conditions, portfolio or asset pool performance or other circumstances or developments,
after the date of this prospectus, except to the extent required by applicable law.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="sp1_003"></A>[Notice
to Investors in the United Kingdom</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in">THIS PROSPECTUS IS NOT A
PROSPECTUS FOR THE PURPOSE OF REGULATION (EU) 2017/1129 (AS AMENDED), <FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">as it forms part of THE
domestic law OF THE UNITED KINGDOM </FONT>(&quot;UK&quot;) <FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">by virtue of the European Union (Withdrawal)
Act 2018 (</FONT>AS AMENDED<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">, the </FONT>&quot;EUWA&quot;<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">)
(</FONT>AS AMENDED<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">, THE &quot;UK PROSPECTUS REGULATION&quot;). </FONT>THIS PROSPECTUS HAS BEEN
PREPARED ON THE BASIS THAT ANY OFFER OF NOTES IN THE UK WILL BE MADE ONLY TO A QUALIFIED INVESTOR AS DEFINED IN ARTICLE&nbsp;2 OF THE
UK PROSPECTUS REGULATION (<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">&quot;UK QUALIFIED INVESTOR&quot;</FONT>). ACCORDINGLY, ANY PERSON
MAKING OR INTENDING TO MAKE AN OFFER IN THE UK OF NOTES WHICH ARE THE SUBJECT OF THE OFFERING CONTEMPLATED IN THIS PROSPECTUS MAY&nbsp;ONLY
DO SO WITH RESPECT TO UK QUALIFIED INVESTORS. NONE OF THE TRUST, THE DEPOSITORS NOR ANY UNDERWRITER HAS AUTHORIZED, NOR DO THEY AUTHORIZE,
THE MAKING OF ANY OFFER OF NOTES IN THE UK OTHER THAN TO UK QUALIFIED INVESTORS.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase">The
Notes are not intended to be offered, sold or otherwise made available to and should not be offered, sold or otherwise made available
to any retail investor in the UK. For these purposes, a retail investor means a person who is one (or more) of: (i)&nbsp;a retail client,
as defined in point (8)&nbsp;of Article&nbsp;2 of COMMISSION DELEGATED Regulation (EU) No 2017/565, as it forms part of UK domestic law
by</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase"></FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 5; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->4<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase">virtue of the eUWA or (ii)&nbsp;a customer within the meaning of the provisions of the UNITED KINGDOM FINANCIAL SERVICES AND MARKETS
ACT 2000 (AS AMENDED, THE </FONT>&quot;FSMA&quot;<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">) and any rules&nbsp;or regulations made under
the FSMA to implement </FONT>DIRECTIVE (EU) 2016/97 (AS AMENDED, KNOWN AS THE &quot;INSURANCE DISTRIBUTION DIRECTIVE&quot;)<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">,
where that customer would not qualify as a professional client, as defined in point (8)&nbsp;of Article&nbsp;2(1)&nbsp;of Regulation
(EU) No 600/2014, as it forms part of UK domestic law by virtue of the EUWA or (iii)&nbsp;not a uk qualified investor.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt; text-transform: uppercase">Consequently
no key information document required by </FONT>REGULATION (EU) NO 1286/2014 (AS AMENDED)<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">, as
it forms part of UK domestic law by virtue of the EUWA (AS AMENDED, the </FONT>&quot;UK PRIIPS REGULATION&quot;<FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase">)
for offering or selling the Notes or otherwise making them available to retail investors in the UK has been prepared and therefore offering
or selling the Notes or otherwise making them available to any retail investor in the UK may be unlawful under the UK PRIIPs Regulation.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">THIS PROSPECTUS
IS DIRECTED IN THE UK ONLY AT PERSONS WHO (I)&nbsp;ARE AUTHORIZED TO CARRY ON A REGULATED ACTIVITY UNDER FSMA, (II)&nbsp;HAVE PROFESSIONAL
EXPERIENCE IN MATTERS RELATING TO INVESTMENTS AND WHO QUALIFY AS INVESTMENT PROFESSIONALS UNDER ARTICLE&nbsp;19(5)&nbsp;OF THE UNITED
KINGDOM FINANCIAL SERVICES AND MARKETS ACT 2000 (FINANCIAL PROMOTION) ORDER 2005 (THE &quot;FPO&quot;), (III)&nbsp;ARE HIGH NET WORTH
COMPANIES, UNINCORPORATED ASSOCIATIONS, PARTNERSHIPS OR TRUSTEES UNDER ARTICLE&nbsp;49(2)&nbsp;OF THE FPO OR (IV)&nbsp;ARE PERSONS TO
WHOM THIS PROSPECTUS MAY&nbsp;OTHERWISE LAWFULLY BE DIRECTED (TOGETHER, &quot;RELEVANT PERSONS&quot;). IN THE UK, THIS PROSPECTUS MUST
NOT BE ACTED ON OR RELIED ON BY PERSONS WHO ARE NOT RELEVANT PERSONS AND ONLY RELEVANT PERSONS MAY&nbsp;INVEST IN THE NOTES. IN THE UK,
ANY INVESTMENT ACTIVITY RELATING TO THIS PROSPECTUS OR THE NOTES WILL BE ENGAGED IN ONLY WITH RELEVANT PERSONS. THE COMMUNICATION OF
THIS PROSPECTUS TO ANY PERSON IN THE UK OTHER THAN A RELEVANT PERSON IS UNAUTHORIZED AND MAY&nbsp;CONTRAVENE FSMA</FONT>.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">POTENTIAL INVESTORS IN THE UK ARE ADVISED THAT
ALL, OR MOST, OF THE PROTECTIONS AFFORDED BY THE UK REGULATORY SYSTEM WILL NOT APPLY TO AN INVESTMENT IN THE NOTES AND THAT COMPENSATION
WILL NOT BE AVAILABLE UNDER THE UK FINANCIAL SERVICES COMPENSATION SCHEME.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="sp1_004"></A>[Notice
to Investors in the European Economic Area</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">THIS PROSPECTUS IS NOT A PROSPECTUS FOR THE PURPOSE
OF REGULATION (EU) 2017/1129 (AS AMENDED, THE &quot;PROSPECTUS REGULATION&quot;). THIS PROSPECTUS HAS BEEN PREPARED ON THE BASIS THAT
ANY OFFERS OF THE NOTES IN THE EUROPEAN ECONOMIC AREA (&quot;EEA&quot;) WILL ONLY BE MADE TO A PERSON OR LEGAL ENTITY THAT IS A QUALIFIED
INVESTOR AS DEFINED IN ARTICLE&nbsp;2 OF THE PROSPECTUS REGULATION (&quot;QUALIFIED INVESTOR&quot;). ACCORDINGLY, ANY PERSON MAKING OR
INTENDING TO MAKE AN OFFER IN THE EEA OF THE NOTES DESCRIBED IN THIS PROSPECTUS MAY&nbsp;ONLY DO SO WITH RESPECT TO QUALIFIED INVESTORS.
NONE OF THE TRUST, THE DEPOSITORS NOR ANY UNDERWRITER HAS AUTHORIZED, NOR DO THEY AUTHORIZE, THE OFFERING OF THE NOTES IN THE EEA OTHER
THAN TO ONE OR MORE QUALIFIED INVESTORS.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">THE NOTES ARE NOT INTENDED TO BE OFFERED, SOLD
OR OTHERWISE MADE AVAILABLE TO AND SHOULD NOT BE OFFERED, SOLD OR OTHERWISE MADE AVAILABLE TO ANY RETAIL INVESTOR IN THE EEA. FOR THESE
PURPOSES, A RETAIL INVESTOR MEANS A PERSON WHO IS ONE (OR MORE) OF: (I)&nbsp;A RETAIL CLIENT AS DEFINED IN POINT (11) OF ARTICLE&nbsp;4(1)&nbsp;OF
DIRECTIVE 2014/65/EU (AS AMENDED, &quot;MIFID II&quot;); (II)&nbsp;A CUSTOMER WITHIN THE MEANING OF THE INSURANCE DISTRIBUTION DIRECTIVE
WHERE THAT CUSTOMER WOULD NOT QUALIFY AS A PROFESSIONAL CLIENT AS DEFINED IN POINT (10)&nbsp;OF ARTICLE&nbsp;4(1)&nbsp;OF MIFID II; OR
(III)&nbsp;NOT A QUALIFIED INVESTOR AS DEFINED IN THE PROSPECTUS REGULATION.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">CONSEQUENTLY NO
KEY INFORMATION DOCUMENT REQUIRED BY REGULATION (EU) NO 1286/2014 (AS AMENDED, THE &quot;PRIIPS REGULATION&quot;) FOR OFFERING OR SELLING
THE NOTES</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"></FONT></P>

    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">OR OTHERWISE MAKING THEM AVAILABLE TO RETAIL INVESTORS IN THE EEA HAS BEEN PREPARED AND THEREFORE OFFERING OR SELLING THE NOTES
OR OTHERWISE MAKING THEM AVAILABLE TO ANY RETAIL INVESTOR IN THE EEA MAY&nbsp;BE UNLAWFUL UNDER THE PRIIPS REGULATION</FONT>.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

                                            spread for this series is the excess of interest collections allocated to the series over
                                            the interest payments on the notes and the senior fees and expenses of the trust that are
                                            allocated to the series.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><SUP>(2)</SUP></TD><TD>The depositor interest will be held by the depositors and
                                            represents the interest in the trust property not allocated to a series. A portion of the
                                            depositor interest equal to the available subordinated amount is subordinated to the notes.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><SUP>(3)</SUP></TD><TD>The depositors will deposit $_________ in the reserve account
                                            on the closing date. The amount that is required to be in the reserve account is ___% of
                                            the initial note balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes, unless the depositors elect to
                                            increase the amount in the reserve account during a subordination step-up period or an amortization
                                            event occurs in which case the reserve account required amount will increase.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 8pt"><SUP>(4)</SUP></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 8pt">All
                                            notes other than the Class&nbsp;D notes will benefit from subordination of more junior classes
                                            to more senior classes. </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-size: 7.5pt">The subordination varies depending
                                            on whether interest or principal is being paid, whether an amortization event that results
                                            in monthly payments of principal has occurred and whether an event of default that results
                                            in acceleration has occurred. <I>For more details about subordination, you should read &quot;Description
                                            of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees
                                            and Other Items&quot; and &quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor
                                            Collections &mdash; Payment of Principal&quot; and &quot;Credit Enhancement &mdash; Subordination</I></FONT><I>.<FONT STYLE="font-size: 7.5pt">&quot;</FONT></I></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><SUP>(5)</SUP></TD><TD>The aggregate principal amount of each class of notes may
                                            be increased or decreased, pro rata, on or before the day of pricing. Any dollar amounts
                                            in this prospectus that are calculated based on the principal amount of the notes will be
                                            similarly increased or decreased, pro rata.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<DIV STYLE="border: Black 1pt solid; padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 5pt; width: 99%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="sp2a_001"></A>Summary</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I>This summary describes the main terms of the
issuance of and payments on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes, the assets of the trust, the cash flows of the series and the credit enhancement
available for the series. It does not contain all of the information that you should consider in making your decision to purchase any
notes. To understand fully the terms of the notes and the transaction structure, you should read this prospectus completely, especially
 &quot;Risk Factors&quot; starting on page&nbsp;__.</I></P>

<DIV STYLE="float: left; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Transaction Overview</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust is a master trust that owns a revolving pool of receivables
originated in connection with the purchase and financing of new and used car, truck and utility vehicle inventory by motor vehicle dealers.
The trust will issue the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes backed by this revolving pool of receivables to the depositors on the closing date.
The depositors will sell the offered notes to the underwriters, who will offer and sell the offered notes to investors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Transaction Parties</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Sponsor, Servicer and Administrator of the Trust</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Ford Motor Credit Company LLC, or &quot;Ford Credit,&quot; is a Delaware
limited liability company and a wholly-owned subsidiary of Ford Motor Company, or &quot;Ford.&quot;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Depositors</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Ford Credit Floorplan Corporation, or &quot;FCF Corp,&quot; a Delaware
corporation, and Ford Credit Floorplan LLC, or &quot;FCF LLC,&quot; a Delaware limited liability company, are special-purpose companies
wholly owned by Ford Credit.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Issuing Entity or Trust</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Ford Credit Floorplan Master Owner Trust A, or the &quot;trust,&quot;
is a Delaware statutory trust established under a trust agreement between the depositors and the owner trustee.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Owner Trustee</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: italic 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal">U.S.
Bank Trust National Association</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Indenture Trustee</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt">The
Bank of New York Mellon</FONT></P>

</DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<DIV STYLE="float: right; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Back-up Servicer</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt">Computershare
Trust Company, N.A., or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt">&quot;Computershare
Trust Company.&quot;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Asset Representations Reviewer</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">[The Class&nbsp;A-1 and Class&nbsp;A-2 notes are together referred to
as the &quot;Class&nbsp;A notes.&quot;] [The Class&nbsp;A [and Class&nbsp;B] notes are being offered by this prospectus and are also referred
to as the &quot;offered notes&quot; and, together with the [Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D notes], the &quot;Series&nbsp;20__-__
notes,&quot; the &quot;notes.&quot;] [The Class&nbsp;A[-1, Class&nbsp;A-2 Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D] notes are sometimes
referred to as the &quot;fixed rate notes.&quot;] [The Class&nbsp;A[-1, A-2, Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D] notes are sometimes
referred to as the &quot;floating rate notes.&quot;] [The Class&nbsp;A-1 and Class&nbsp;A-2 notes have equal rights to interest and principal
payments and, unless stated in this prospectus, will be treated as a single class in relation to the other classes.]</P>

 &quot;step-up amounts&quot; will be paid on each class of notes at a per annum &quot;step-up rate&quot; equal to, for the fixed rate notes,
the related interest rate less ___% and, for the floating rate notes, the excess of the related interest rate over the related benchmark.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Form&nbsp;and Minimum Denomination</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The notes will be issued in book-entry form. The offered notes will
be available in minimum denominations of [$1,000] and in integral multiples of [$1,000].</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Payment Dates [and Step-Up Amounts; Interest Accrual]</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust will pay interest and, [following the expected final payment
date, step-up amounts] on the notes on &quot;payment dates,&quot; which will be the 15th day of each month (or, if not a business day,
the next business day). The first payment date will be ________, 20__.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">[Interest on the fixed rate notes [and any related step-up amounts]
will accrue on a &quot;30/360&quot; basis from the 15th day of the prior month to the 15th day of the current month (or from the closing
date to ________, 20__, for the first period).] [Interest on the floating rate notes and any related step-up amounts will accrue on an
 &quot;actual/360&quot; basis from the prior payment date (or from the closing date, for the first period) to the current payment date.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more details about the payment of interest and step-up amounts
on the notes, you should read &quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Payments of Interest and Step-Up Amounts.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>[Calculation Agent</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The &quot;calculation agent&quot; will be the indenture trustee. The
calculation agent will determine 30-day average SOFR, which is used to determine the interest rate for the floating rate notes.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>[Optional Redemption</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The notes will be subject to redemption, in whole but not in part, at
the option of the trust (a)&nbsp;on any payment date beginning with the [__] payment date before the expected final payment date, or the
 &quot;note redemption period,&quot; without a make-whole payment or (b)&nbsp;on any earlier payment date, with a make-whole payment.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">On the exercise of the optional redemption
and payment of an </FONT>amount sufficient to pay the notes in full, including all accrued and unpaid interest, principal, any applicable
make-whole payments [or step-up amounts] due, and all fees and expenses of the trust payable under the indenture supplement, the notes
will be redeemed and paid in full.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more information about optional
redemption, you should read &quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Optional Redemption</I></FONT>.<I>&quot;</I>]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>[Make-Whole Payments</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">A make-whole payment will be due on each principal payment made prior
to the start of the note redemption period as a result of the occurrence of the trust's exercise of its option to redeem the notes prior
to the note redemption period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more details about the make-whole
payments, you should read &quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Make-Whole Payments.&quot;</I></FONT>]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Trust Property</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The primary asset of the trust is a revolving pool of receivables and
related assets originated in accounts designated to the trust. On ________, 20__, the total principal balance of the receivables was $___________.
The number of designated accounts was _____.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more information about the accounts and receivables in the trust,
you should read &quot;Trust Property.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Servicing</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Ford Credit will be the &quot;servicer&quot; of the receivables and
of this securitization transaction. The servicer is responsible for collecting and recording payments, making required</P>

</DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<DIV STYLE="float: right; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">adjustments to
the receivables, monitoring dealer payments and maintaining books and records relating to the accounts and the receivables. The servicer
will prepare monthly reports on the accounts and the receivables, payments on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes and the status of credit enhancements.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust will pay the servicer a fee each month equal to 1/12 of ___%
of the portion of the receivables allocated to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more information about the servicer, you should read &quot;Sponsor
and Servicer.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">[__________ is the back-up servicer. The back-up servicer will periodically
review the servicer's operations (the frequency of which will depend on the servicer's long-term, unsecured debt ratings), receive monthly
receivables data and confirm certain information on the monthly investor reports. If the servicer resigns or is terminated, the back-up
servicer will be the successor servicer.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust will pay the back-up servicer a fee each month equal to 1/12
of ___% of the portion of the receivables allocated to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more information about the back-up
servicer, you should read &quot;Transaction Parties &mdash; Back-up Servicer.&quot;</I></FONT>]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Allocation of Collections</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The servicer will collect payments on the receivables and will deposit
these collections, up to the amount required for payment to each series on the following payment date, in the collection account. Each
month, the servicer will allocate interest collections, principal collections and the principal balance of defaulted receivables to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more details about the application of interest collections, you
should read &quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Principal Collections</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The application of principal collections allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__
on each payment date will depend on whether it is in the revolving period, the [controlled accumulation period,] required amortization
period or the early amortization period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Revolving Period. </I>The revolving period for the series starts on the
closing date and ends when the [controlled accumulation period, ]required amortization period or the early amortization period starts.
During the revolving period, no principal will be paid to or accumulated for the series. Instead, principal collections allocated to the
series will be (1)&nbsp;used to pay principal and make deposits for other series in principal sharing group one, (2)&nbsp;deposited in
the excess funding account, (3)&nbsp;during an excess funding period, applied to cover shortfalls under items (1)&nbsp;to (6)&nbsp;of
<I>&quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I>
and (4)&nbsp;paid to the depositors.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Amortization Periods. </I>The [controlled accumulation period, ] required
amortization period for the series will start on the expected final payment date and will end on the earliest of (a)&nbsp;the day before
the start of the early amortization period, (b)&nbsp;the end of the month before the payment date on which the notes will be paid in full
and (c)&nbsp;the final maturity date. If an amortization event occurs, the early amortization period will start. On each payment date
during the [controlled accumulation period, ] required amortization period or an early amortization period, (1)&nbsp;principal collections
allocated to the series and (2)&nbsp;collections allocated to the portion of the depositor interest that is subordinated to the series
(in the case of principal collections, in an amount not to exceed the available subordinated amount) will be paid to the Series&nbsp;20__-__
noteholders sequentially by class.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more details about the application
of principal collections, you should read</I></FONT></P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="float: right; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I></I></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>&quot;Description of the Notes </I></FONT>&mdash; <I>Application of Investor Collections &mdash;
Payment of Principal.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">[<I>Controlled Accumulation Period. </I>The controlled accumulation period
for the series is scheduled to start _______, 20__, but may start at a later date. On each payment date during the controlled accumulation
period, principal collections allocated to the series will be deposited in the principal funding account up to the controlled accumulation
amount. Any remaining principal collections will be (1)&nbsp;used to pay principal and make deposits for other series in principal sharing
group one, (2)&nbsp;deposited in the excess funding account and (3)&nbsp;paid to the depositors. On the expected final payment date, the
amounts in the principal funding account will be paid to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders sequentially by class.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.25in">An accumulation period reserve account will be established
to provide additional funds to pay interest on the notes during the controlled accumulation period. The accumulation period reserve account
will be funded before the start of the controlled accumulation period from interest collections allocated to the series. The amount required
to be in the accumulation period reserve account will be $_________, which is __% of the initial note balance of the series.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>Early Amortization Period. </I>If an amortization event occurs, the early
amortization period will start. On each payment date during the early amortization period, (1)&nbsp;principal collections allocated to
the series and (2)&nbsp;collections allocated to the portion of the depositor interest that is subordinated to the series (in the case
of principal collections, in an amount not to exceed the available subordinated amount) will be paid to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders
sequentially by class.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

the application of principal collections, you should read &quot;Description of the Notes </I></FONT>&mdash; <I>Application of Investor
Collections &mdash; Payment of Principal.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Amortization Events</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">If the events described below occur, an early amortization period will
start.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The following &quot;series amortization events&quot; only apply to Series&nbsp;20__-__:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">either depositor fails to make a payment or deposit required under the sale
and servicing agreement within five business days,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">either depositor fails to observe or perform a covenant or agreement in a
material respect or its representations are incorrect in a material respect, and the breach is not corrected within 60 days after the
depositor receives notice of the breach, and the breach continues to adversely affect the amount or timing of payments to be made to the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders for that period,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a servicer termination event occurs that adversely affects the amount or timing

invested amounts of all series issued by the trust for three consecutive months, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Events of Default</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Each of the following will be an &quot;event of default&quot; for the
series under the indenture and the indenture supplement:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to pay interest due on any note within 35 days after a payment
date,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to pay the principal of[, make-whole payments on, and any
accrued step-up amounts on] any note in full by its final maturity date,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to observe or perform a material covenant or agreement or
breaches a representation in any material respect that is not corrected within a 60-day cure period, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a bankruptcy or dissolution of the trust.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">If an event of default occurs, other than because of a bankruptcy or
dissolution of the trust, the indenture trustee or a majority of Series&nbsp;20__-__ may accelerate the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes and
declare them immediately due and payable. If an event of default occurs because of a bankruptcy or dissolution of the trust, the Series&nbsp;20__-__
notes will be accelerated automatically<I>.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more details about events of default,
acceleration of the notes and other remedies available to noteholders after an event of default, you should read &quot;</I></FONT><I>Description
of the Notes &mdash; Events of Default and Acceleration.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Credit Enhancement</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Credit enhancement provides protection for the Series&nbsp;20__-__
notes against losses on the receivables and potential shortfalls in the funds available to the trust to make required payments. If the
credit enhancement is not sufficient to cover all amounts payable on the series, the losses will be allocated first, to the</P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="clear: both; width: 100%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

</DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P></DIV>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 18; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->17<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<DIV STYLE="border: Black 1pt solid; padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 5pt; width: 99%"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<DIV STYLE="float: left; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Class&nbsp;D notes,
second, to the Class&nbsp;C notes, third, to the Class&nbsp;B notes, and fourth, to the Class&nbsp;A notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The enhancement described below is available only to Series&nbsp;20__-__.
The series is not entitled to enhancement available to another series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Reserve Account</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">On the closing date, the trust will deposit $_________ in the reserve
account, which is __% of the initial note balance of the series. If the depositors elect to increase the amount required to be in the
reserve account during a subordination step-up period or an amortization event occurs, the amount required to be in the reserve account
will increase. Funds in the reserve account will be available to pay interest on the notes, senior fees and expenses for the series and
to cover defaulted receivables if interest collections allocated to the series are insufficient.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Subordination of Notes</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust will pay interest to [all classes of] the Class&nbsp;A notes
[on a pari passu basis] and then will pay interest sequentially to the remaining classes of notes in order of seniority. The trust will
not pay interest on the Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C or Class&nbsp;D notes until all interest due on the Class&nbsp;A notes is paid in full.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust will pay principal sequentially to each class of notes in
order of seniority. The trust will not pay the principal of any class of notes until the principal amounts of more senior classes of notes
are paid in full.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Subordination of the Depositor Interest</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">A portion of the depositor interest,
or the &quot;available subordinated amount,&quot; is subordinated to the series. The amount subordinated will initially equal $_____________</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-size: 7.5pt">,
</FONT>which is approximately __% of the initial note balance, plus any incremental subordinated amount for the first determination date.
The available subordinated amount will increase during a subordination step-up period, unless the depositors elect to increase the amount
required to be in the reserve account during that period, and is subject to other reductions and increases from time to time.</P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="float: right; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>Excess Spread</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Excess spread for this series is the excess of interest collections
allocated to the series over the interest payments on the notes and the senior fees and expenses of the trust that are allocated to the
series. Any excess spread for this series will be available on each payment date to cover shortfalls in certain items in the priority
of payments, including to offset losses on any defaulted receivables allocated to the series and to make required deposits in the reserve
account.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more information about the credit enhancement for the series,
you should read &quot;Credit Enhancement.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Repurchases of Receivables</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Ford Credit will make representations
about the origination, characteristics and terms of each account and receivable. </FONT>If a representation is later determined to have
been untrue when made, then the receivable was not eligible to be sold to the depositors or the trust. If a breach of a representation
has a material adverse effect on a receivable, the depositors must accept reassignment of the receivables from the trust and Ford Credit
must repurchase the receivable from the depositors unless the breach is corrected before that date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more details about the representations
made about the accounts and receivables and Ford Credit's repurchase obligation if these representations are breached, you should read
 &quot;Trust Property &mdash; Representations About Receivables&quot; and &quot;&mdash; Obligation to Repurchase Receivables&quot;. </I></FONT><I>For
more information about when the asset representations reviewer may review certain accounts and receivables for compliance with the representations,
you should read &quot;Trust Property &mdash; Asset Representations Review.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Sharing Groups</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be included in &quot;excess interest sharing
group one&quot; and in &quot;principal sharing group one.&quot; As part of these groups, Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be entitled in certain
situations to share in excess interest collections and shared principal collections from other series in the same group.</P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="clear: both; width: 100%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

</DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Other Series</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust has issued other series of notes which are secured by the
trust property. Annex A summarizes the main terms of each series issued by the trust.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Ratings</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The depositors expect that the offered notes will receive credit ratings
from ___ nationally recognized statistical rating organizations, or &quot;rating agencies.&quot;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The sponsor has also hired nationally recognized statistical rating
organizations to rate the notes of other series issued by the trust, who are also referred to as &quot;rating agencies&quot; when referring
to ratings of other series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The ratings of the offered notes reflect each rating agency&rsquo;s
assessment of the likelihood of the timely payment of interest on, and the ultimate payment of principal of, the offered notes according
to the notes&rsquo; terms. [The ratings of the notes will not address the likelihood of payment of make-whole payments or step-up amounts
on the notes.] Each rating agency rating the offered notes will monitor the ratings under its normal surveillance process. Ford Credit
has agreed to provide ongoing information about the offered notes and the receivables to each rating agency. A rating agency may change
or withdraw an assigned rating at any time. A rating action taken by one rating agency may not necessarily be taken by another rating
agency. No transaction party will be responsible for monitoring any changes to the ratings on the offered notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Tax Status</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">If you purchase a note, you agree by your purchase that you will treat
your note as debt for U.S. federal, state and local income and franchise tax purposes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Katten Muchin Rosenman LLP will deliver its opinion that, for U.S.
federal income tax purposes:</P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="float: right; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the offered notes will be treated as debt to the extent the offered notes
are treated as beneficially owned by a person other than the sponsor or its affiliates for such purposes, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust will not be classified as an association or publicly traded partnership
taxable as a corporation.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

about the application of U.S. federal, state and local tax laws, you should read &quot;Tax Considerations.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>ERISA Considerations</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The offered notes generally will be eligible for purchase by employee
benefit plans.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more information about the treatment of the notes under ERISA,
you should read &quot;ERISA Considerations.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Credit Risk Retention</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The risk retention regulations in Regulation RR under the Securities
Exchange Act of 1934, or &quot;Exchange Act,&quot; applicable to revolving pool securitizations require the sponsor, either directly or
through its wholly-owned affiliates, to retain an economic interest of at least 5% in the credit risk of the receivables. The sponsor
will satisfy this credit risk retention requirement by causing the depositors to retain a &quot;seller's interest&quot; of not less than
5% of the principal amount of the notes of each series, including this series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><I>For more information about the manner in which the risk retention
requirements will be satisfied, you should read &quot;Credit Risk Retention.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>[EEA Credit Risk Retention</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">Legislation in the European Economic Area, or &quot;EEA,&quot; permits
some EEA-regulated entities to invest in securitizations only if a sponsor, originator or original lender for the securitization retains,
on an ongoing basis, a material net economic interest of not less than 5% of the nominal amount of the securitized exposures. Ford Credit,
as originator for this purpose, will retain, on a consolidated basis with the depositors, the depositor interest, which meets these requirements.</P>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="clear: both; width: 100%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

</DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P></DIV>

<DIV STYLE="float: left; width: 48%">

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">In addition, the legislation imposes due diligence and ongoing monitoring
obligations on the affected investors for the securitization transaction and the securitized exposures. Affected investors are solely
responsible for compliance with these additional obligations.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Investment Considerations</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The trust is not registered or required to be registered as an &quot;investment
company&quot; under the Investment Company Act of 1940 and, in making this determination, is relying on the exemption in [Rule&nbsp;3a-7]
under the Investment Company Act of 1940, although other exclusions or exemptions may also be available to the trust. The trust is structured
not to be a &quot;covered fund&quot; under the regulations adopted to implement Section&nbsp;619 of the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform
and Consumer Protection Act, commonly known as the Volcker Rule.</P>

It does not contain all of the information regarding the risks that you should consider in making your decision to purchase any notes.

<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">ability of the servicer to change the terms of the receivables,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">decreases in the credit quality of the trust property resulting from changing
receivables,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the security interest of the trust in a receivable or financed vehicle is
not perfected or is of lower priority than another security interest,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">changes in the rate of sales for vehicle models or vehicle types or certain
economic or other factors affecting a state or region, in each case, with a high concentration of the trust&rsquo;s assets,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">failure by Ford to pay adjustment fees to the servicer for any in-transit
receivables, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">terminations of dealer financial assistance or failures to repurchase by Ford
or Ford Credit.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Risks relating to macroeconomic, regulatory and other external factors</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The notes are subject to risks relating to climate change, the broader
economy, legal and regulatory environment and other external factors, which could lead to shortfalls in payments or losses on your notes,
adversely affect the market value of your notes and/or limit your ability to resell your notes, including:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">climate related legislation and regulation, the physical effects of climate
change, and any associated reputational risk,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a significant global or regional event, such as a financial crisis, economic
downturn or recession, a public health crisis, epidemic or pandemic, a natural disaster or a geopolitical conflict, war or other military
conflict,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">[the use of SOFR, a relatively new reference rate, for the floating rate notes,
and]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">legal and regulatory developments affecting the automotive or financial services
sectors.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Risks relating to the transaction parties</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">The notes are subject to risks relating to the various transaction parties
that are involved in the structuring and ongoing maintenance of the transaction and the offering of the notes, which could lead to shortfalls
in payments or losses on your notes, adversely affect the market value of your notes and/or limit your ability to resell your notes, including:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">declines in the financial condition or business prospects, including bankruptcy,
of Ford or Ford Credit,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.2in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">ability of the servicer to commingle collections with its own funds for a
certain period of time,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 18pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 13.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">delays in collecting payments if Ford Credit is not the servicer or an insufficient
monthly servicing fee to attract a successor servicer, if necessary, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 18pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 13.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">cybersecurity incidents and other disruptions to the servicer&rsquo;s operational
information systems and security systems.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>
