<TD STYLE="width: 0.75in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">paid to the depositors.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">(4)</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>investor percentage of principal collections allocated to each series in the [controlled
accumulation period, ]required amortization period or an early amortization period will be deposited in the collection account for application
and payment.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;net adjusted pool balance&quot; will
be the sum of (a)&nbsp;the adjusted pool balance, plus (b)&nbsp;during an accumulation period or amortization period for any series, principal
collections in the collection account allocable to a series, plus (c)&nbsp;the amount in the principal funding accounts for all series
(other than net investment earnings).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Principal payments also may be funded from proceeds
from the issuance of a new series in the same principal sharing group.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_031"></A>Defaulted Receivables and Principal Collections Used to Pay Interest</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Defaulted receivables will be allocated to each
series and the depositor interest in the same manner as principal and interest collections as described in <I>&quot;&mdash; Investor Percentage
and Depositor Percentage&quot;</I> above. A &quot;defaulted receivable&quot; is a receivable that (a)&nbsp;was charged off as uncollectible
according to the servicer's policies and procedures or (b)&nbsp;remains outstanding and owned by the trust for more than six months after
the date the related account was classified as &quot;status,&quot; as described in <I>&quot;Sponsor and Servicer </I>&mdash; <I>Servicing
and Dealer Relations &mdash; Dealer Status.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The defaulted receivables allocated to a series
may be reimbursed from interest collections allocable to that series and other amounts available to make payments pursuant to the priority
of payments as described in <I>&quot;&mdash; Allocation and Application of Collections&quot;</I> above and in <I>&quot;Description of
the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items.&quot;</I> Amounts applied to</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 77; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->76<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0">reimburse defaulted receivables will be treated as principal collections and applied as described in <I>&quot;&mdash; Allocation and Application
of Collections&quot;</I> above and in <I>&quot;Description of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of
Principal.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If the available subordinated amount for a series
is reduced to zero, the invested amount for that series will be reduced by defaulted receivables not reimbursed by interest collections.
In addition, the invested amount for a series will be reduced by the amount of any principal collections used to pay interest on the notes
of that series. Reductions in the invested amount for a series due to defaulted receivables not reimbursed by interest collections and
any principal collections used to pay interest will be reimbursed on any later payment date to the extent that interest collections allocable
to that series exceed the interest owed on the notes, the defaulted receivables allocated to the series and other fees and expenses that
are payable on that date. This reimbursement will increase the invested amount for that series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_032"></A>Excess Funding Account</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The indenture trustee established an &quot;excess
funding account&quot; for the benefit of the noteholders of all series. Deposits will be made in the excess funding account from collections
allocable to the depositor interest so that the net adjusted pool balance is at least equal to the required pool balance. If, on the issuance
of a series, the net adjusted pool balance would be less than the required pool balance, then a portion of the proceeds of the issuance
equal to the amount of the shortfall will be deposited in the excess funding account.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If, on repurchase of a receivable by the depositors,
the depositor amount would be less than the required depositor amount, the depositors will deposit the shortfall in the excess funding
account, as described in <I>&quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations &mdash; Required Depositor Amount</I>.<I>&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If the servicer adjusts the principal balance of
a receivable because of a rebate to the dealer, a billing error or other reason, the pool balance and the depositor amount will be increased
or decreased by the amount of the adjustment. If any decrease in the depositor amount would cause it to fall below the required depositor
amount, the depositors will deposit the shortfall in the excess funding account on the day of the adjustment.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">In addition, the depositors may direct the servicer
and the indenture trustee to deposit amounts payable to them in the excess funding account. If the net adjusted pool balance exceeds the
required pool balance, the servicer may instruct the indenture trustee to withdraw the excess from the excess funding account and pay
it to the depositors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If an amortization period or accumulation period
starts for a series, the amounts in the excess funding account that are allocable to the series will be held for payment to the noteholders
of that series on the dates stated in this prospectus or accumulated for payment on the expected final payment date. These amounts will
be paid to the noteholders of the series or held for and paid to the noteholders of other series as described in <I>&quot;Description
of the Notes &mdash; Application of Investor Collections.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">An &quot;excess funding period&quot; will occur
during any payment dates for which the amount in the excess funding account exceeds 30% of the sum of the adjusted invested amounts of
all series for the related month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="text-transform: uppercase"><B><A NAME="ab_033"></A>Description
of the Notes</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>The trust will
issue the notes under the indenture and the indenture supplement</I></FONT><I> between the trust and the indenture trustee. The following
description summarizes the main terms of the notes and the indenture but is not a complete description of the notes or the transaction
documents. For more details about the notes and the transaction documents, you should read this prospectus as well as the indenture, the
form of the indenture supplement, the sale and servicing agreements, the receivables purchase</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I>&nbsp;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I></I></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->77<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0"><I>agreements and the trust agreement that
are included as exhibits to the registration statement filed with the SEC that includes this prospectus.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_034"></A>General</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The Class&nbsp;A, Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and
Class&nbsp;D notes are the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes and will be issued under the indenture, as supplemented by the Series&nbsp;20__-__
indenture supplement, between the trust and the indenture trustee. The notes will be issued in minimum denominations of $1,000 and in
integral multiples of $1,000 and will be available only in book-entry form.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_035"></A>Payments of Interest[ and Step-Up Amounts]</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>General</I></B></FONT>.
The trust will pay interest on the notes on each payment date. The interest rate for the floating rate notes will be determined as described
below under &quot;<I>&mdash; Floating Rate Benchmark Rate; Benchmark Transition Event</I>.&quot; [In addition, after the expected final
payment date, the trust will pay step-up amounts on the notes of each class on a subordinated basis at a per annum step-up rate equal
to, for the fixed rate notes, the related interest rate less 0.01% and, for the floating rate notes, the excess of the related interest
rate over the related benchmark.] Interest on the fixed rate notes [and any related step-up amounts] will be based on a 360-day year consisting
of twelve 30-day months. Interest on the floating rate notes[ and any related step-up amounts] will be calculated based on the actual
number of days in the interest period and a 360-day year. Interest on each class of notes will be calculated based on its note balance
as of the end of the prior interest period, except that interest for the first payment date will be calculated on the initial note balance
of each class of notes. The &quot;payment date&quot; will be the 15th day of each month (or, if not a business day, the next business
day) and the first payment date will be [__].</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">All interest [and step-up amounts] due but not
paid on a payment date will be due on the next payment date, together with interest on the unpaid amount at the applicable interest rate.
[Step-up amounts will not be paid on any class of notes until all principal amounts payable on that payment date from interest collections
have been paid in full. Any unpaid step-up amounts on the notes will be payable in full on the final maturity date or any optional redemption
date on which the notes are required to be paid in full. Failure to pay step-up amounts on any notes on any payment date will not be an
event of default until the final maturity date.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be included in excess
interest sharing group one and will in certain situations be entitled to share in excess interest collections that are allocated to other
series in the same group. <I>For more information on excess interest sharing group one, you should read &quot;&mdash; Groups &mdash; Excess
Interest Sharing Group One&quot; below.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>[<I>Floating Rate
Benchmark Rate; Benchmark Transition Event.</I></B></FONT> Interest on the floating rate notes will accrue at a floating rate based on
a benchmark rate initially based on the secured overnight financing rate, or &quot;SOFR,&quot; published by the FRBNY but will be replaced
by the benchmark replacement following the occurrence of a benchmark transition event and its related benchmark replacement date as described
below. The benchmark rate will initially be &quot;30-day average SOFR,&quot; which for any determination date is the average of the daily
SOFR for the preceding 30 calendar days, compounded daily on SOFR business days. The 30-day average SOFR rate will be obtained by the
calculation agent for each interest period by referring to a published source of the rate. The calculation agent will obtain 30-day average
SOFR for each interest period on the &quot;SOFR determination date,&quot; which is the second SOFR business day before that interest period.
If a published 30-day average SOFR rate is unavailable on a SOFR determination date, the rate will be the 30-day average SOFR for the
most recent SOFR business day on which such rate was published. For purposes of calculating the SOFR rate, a &quot;SOFR business day&quot;
means a business day determined in accordance with the SOFR publication calendar of the FRBNY. All determinations of 30-day average SOFR
by the calculation agent, in absence of manifest error, will be conclusive and binding on the noteholders.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the trust determines
that a benchmark transition event and its related benchmark replacement date have occurred prior to the SOFR determination date or otherwise</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 79; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->78<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0">prior to the determination date of the then-current benchmark, the benchmark replacement will replace the then-current benchmark for all
purposes relating to the floating rate notes in respect of such determination on such date and all determinations on all subsequent dates.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A &quot;benchmark transition event&quot; means
the occurrence of one or more of the following events with respect to the then-current benchmark:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(1)</TD><TD>a public statement or publication of information by or on behalf of the administrator of the benchmark announcing that such administrator
has ceased or will cease to provide the benchmark, permanently or indefinitely; provided, that, at the time of such statement or publication,
there is no successor administrator that will continue to provide the benchmark,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(2)</TD><TD>a public statement or publication of information by the regulatory supervisor for the administrator of the benchmark, the central
bank for the currency of the benchmark, an insolvency official with jurisdiction over the administrator for the benchmark, a resolution
authority with jurisdiction over the administrator for the benchmark or a court or an entity with similar insolvency or resolution authority
over the administrator for the benchmark, which states that the administrator of the benchmark has ceased or will cease to provide the
benchmark permanently or indefinitely; provided, that, at the time of such statement or publication, there is no successor administrator
that will continue to provide the benchmark, or</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(3)</TD><TD>a public statement or publication of information by the regulatory supervisor for the administrator of the benchmark announcing that
the benchmark is no longer representative of the underlying market or economic reality or may no longer be used.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A &quot;benchmark replacement date&quot; means:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(1)</TD><TD>in the case of clause (1)&nbsp;or (2)&nbsp;of the definition of benchmark transition event, the later of (a)&nbsp;the date of the
public statement or publication of information referenced therein and (b)&nbsp;the date on which the administrator of the benchmark permanently
or indefinitely ceases to provide the benchmark, or</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(2)</TD><TD>in the case of clause (3)&nbsp;of the definition of benchmark transition event, the date of the public statement or publication of
information referenced therein.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>&quot;benchmark
replacement&quot; will be the first alternative set forth in the order below that can be determined by the trust as of the benchmark replacement
date:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(1)</TD><TD>the sum of (a)&nbsp;the alternate rate of interest that has been selected or recommended by the relevant governmental body as the
replacement for the then-current benchmark for the applicable corresponding tenor and (b)&nbsp;the benchmark replacement adjustment, or</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(2)</TD><TD>the sum of (a)&nbsp;the alternate rate of interest that has been selected by the trust in its reasonable discretion as the replacement
for the then-current benchmark for the applicable corresponding tenor and (b)&nbsp;the benchmark replacement adjustment.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>&quot;corresponding
tenor&quot; will be a tenor (including overnight) having approximately the same length (disregarding business day adjustment) as the applicable
tenor for the then-current benchmark.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>&quot;benchmark
replacement adjustment&quot; will be the first alternative set forth in the order below that can be determined by the trust as of the
benchmark replacement date:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(1)</TD><TD>the spread adjustment (which may be a positive or negative value or zero), or method for calculating or determining such spread adjustment,
that has been selected or </TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 80; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->79<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt">
  <TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 27pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>recommended by the relevant governmental body for the applicable unadjusted benchmark replacement, or</TD></TR>
  </TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 27pt">(2)</TD><TD>the spread adjustment (which may be a positive or negative value or zero), or method for calculating or determining such spread adjustment,
that has been selected by the trust in its reasonable discretion for the replacement of the then-current benchmark with the applicable
unadjusted benchmark replacement.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>&quot;unadjusted
benchmark replacement&quot; is the benchmark replacement excluding the benchmark replacement adjustment.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The </FONT>&quot;relevant
governmental body&quot; is the Federal Reserve Board and/or the FRBNY, or a committee officially endorsed or convened by the Federal Reserve
Board and/or the FRBNY, or any successor thereto.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">In connection with
the implementation of a benchmark replacement, the trust will have the right from time to time to make </FONT>&quot;benchmark replacement
conforming changes,&quot; which are any technical, administrative or operational changes (including changes to the timing and frequency
of determining rates, the process of making payments of interest, rounding of amounts or tenors, and other administrative matters) that
the trust decides may be appropriate to reflect the adoption of such benchmark replacement in a manner substantially consistent with market
practice (or, if the trust decides that adoption of any portion of such market practice is not administratively feasible or if the trust
determines that no market practice for use of the benchmark replacement exists, in such other manner as the trust determines is reasonably
necessary).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Notice of the occurrence of a benchmark transition
event and its related benchmark replacement date, the determination of a benchmark replacement and the making of any benchmark conforming
changes will be included in the monthly investor report. Notwithstanding anything in the transaction documents to the contrary, upon the
inclusion of such information in the monthly investor report, the relevant transaction documents will be deemed to have been amended to
reflect the new unadjusted benchmark replacement, benchmark replacement adjustment and/or benchmark replacement conforming changes without
further compliance with the amendment provisions of the relevant transaction documents.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Any determination, decision or election that may
be made by the trust in connection with a benchmark transition event or a benchmark replacement as described above, including any determination
with respect to a tenor, rate or adjustment or of the occurrence or non-occurrence of an event, circumstance or date and any decision
to take or refrain from taking any action or any selection, will be conclusive and binding absent manifest error, may be made in the trust's
sole discretion, and, notwithstanding anything to the contrary in the transaction documents, will become effective without consent from
any other party. None of the trust, the owner trustee, the indenture trustee, the calculation agent, the administrator, the sponsor, the
depositors or the servicer will have any liability for any determination made by or on behalf of the trust in connection with a benchmark
transition event or a benchmark replacement as described above, and each noteholder, by its acceptance of a note or a beneficial interest
in a note, will be deemed to waive and release any and all claims against the trust, the owner trustee, the indenture trustee, the calculation
agent, the administrator, the sponsor, the depositors or the servicer relating to any such determinations.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_036"></A>Payments of Principal</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The trust expects to pay the principal of the Series&nbsp;20__-__
notes in full on the expected final payment date, which is listed on the cover of this prospectus. However, the trust may pay principal
earlier or later than the expected final payment date if an amortization event occurs. Principal will be paid sequentially to each class
in the order of seniority. The trust will not pay principal of any class until the principal amounts of all more senior classes are paid
in full. If a class of notes is not paid in full on its expected final payment date, an amortization event will occur. Principal will
be paid on the notes monthly</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 81; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->80<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<!-- Field: Split-Segment; Name: 4 -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">on each payment date during the [controlled accumulation period, ]required amortization period and the early
amortization period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The trust will pay principal of the notes on a
payment date from available investor principal collections and, in certain circumstances, available depositor collections deposited in
the &quot;principal funding account&quot; established by the indenture trustee for Series&nbsp;20__-__. The amount of available investor
principal collections and available depositor collections applied to the notes on each payment date will depend on whether the notes are
in the revolving period, the [controlled accumulation period, ]required amortization period or the early amortization period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be included in principal
sharing group one and will be entitled in certain situations to share in excess principal collections that are allocated to other series
in the same group.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more information
about principal sharing group one, you should read &quot;</I></FONT><I>&mdash; Groups &mdash; Principal Sharing Group One&quot; below.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Revolving Period</I></B></FONT>.
The revolving period for Series&nbsp;20__-__ will start on the closing date and end on the day before the [controlled accumulation period,
] required amortization period or the early amortization period starts. During the revolving period, no principal will be accumulated
for or paid on the notes. Instead, available investor principal collections will be applied as described in items (2)&nbsp;to (5)&nbsp;of
<I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Principal&quot;</I> below.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Amortization
Periods</I></B></FONT>. The [controlled accumulation period, ] required amortization period for Series&nbsp;20__-__ will start on the
expected final payment date and will end on the earliest of (1)&nbsp;the day before the start of the early amortization period, (2)&nbsp;the
end of the month before the payment date on which the notes will be paid in full and (3)&nbsp;the final maturity date listed on the cover
of this prospectus.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>[<I>Controlled
Accumulation Period</I></B></FONT>. The controlled accumulation period for Series&nbsp;20__-__ is scheduled to start on _______, 20__,
and is scheduled to last six months. However, the trust may extend the revolving period and postpone the start of the controlled accumulation
period if it expects to be able to fund the principal funding account in full in less than six months. Each month, starting in ______,
20__, and ending when the controlled accumulation period starts, the trust will review the amount of expected principal collections and
determine the number of months expected to be required to fully fund the principal funding account. In making this determination, the
trust must use the lowest monthly payment rate for the prior twelve months and take into account the amount of principal expected to be
allocated to all other series in principal sharing group one that are expected to be amortizing or accumulating principal during the controlled
accumulation period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The controlled accumulation period will end on
the earlier of:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the end of the month before the payment date on which the notes will be paid
in full, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the day before the early amortization period starts.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If an amortization event occurs before the controlled
accumulation period starts, there will be no controlled accumulation period and the early amortization period will start.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On the first business day of the controlled accumulation
period, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ excess funding amount at the end of the revolving period (together with other amounts in the excess funding
account that are allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ as shared principal collections) will be deposited in the principal funding account,
but only to the extent of the controlled accumulation amount<I>. </I>The &quot;controlled accumulation amount&quot; will be $____________,
but will be higher if the controlled accumulation period is postponed, as described above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 82; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->81<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;Series&nbsp;20__-__ excess funding amount&quot;
equals the product of (a)&nbsp;the amount in the excess funding account, times (b)(i)&nbsp;the adjusted invested amount of the notes,
divided by (ii)&nbsp;the sum of the adjusted invested amounts of each series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>For more information
about how invested amount and adjusted invested amount are determined, you should read &quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations</I></FONT><I>
 &mdash; Investor Percentage and Depositor Percentage.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On each payment date in the controlled accumulation
period, the indenture trustee will deposit available investor principal collections (including shared principal collections) in the principal
funding account, as described in item (1)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Principal&quot;
</I>below.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On the expected final payment date (unless paid
earlier during the early amortization period), the trust will pay all amounts in the principal funding account sequentially to each class
in order of seniority until the notes have been paid in full.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>Accumulation Period
Reserve Account</I></FONT>. The indenture trustee will establish the &quot;accumulation period reserve account&quot; for the benefit of
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders to assist with the payment of interest on the notes during the controlled accumulation period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Starting on the payment date occurring in the second
month before the start of the controlled accumulation period, after making other required payments and deposits, the indenture trustee
will deposit available investor interest collections and excess interest collections available for the series from other series in excess
sharing group one in the accumulation period reserve account in an amount equal to $__________, which is __% of the initial note balance
of the series, as described in item (11) of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections </I>&mdash; <I>Payment of Interest, Fees
and Other Items&quot;</I> below.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On each payment date in the controlled accumulation
period, the indenture trustee will withdraw from the accumulation period reserve account and deposit in the collection account to the
extent available an amount equal to the excess of (a)&nbsp;one-twelfth of the product of (i)&nbsp;the amount in the principal funding
account on the prior payment date times (ii)&nbsp;the weighted average note interest rate, over (b)&nbsp;the net investment earnings from
the reserve account, principal funding account and accumulation period reserve account for that payment date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Amounts withdrawn from the accumulation period
reserve account will be included in available investor interest collections.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On the earliest of the first payment date in the
early amortization period, the payment in full of the notes, and the final maturity date, any funds remaining in the accumulation period
reserve account will be included as available investor interest collections.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><I>Early Amortization
Period</I></FONT>. The early amortization period for Series&nbsp;20__-__ will start on the day an amortization event occurs or, if the
servicer is not required to make daily deposits in the collection account, on the first day of the month in which an amortization event
occurs, and will end on the earlier of:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

in an</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_037"></A>Investor Percentages</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The servicer will allocate all collections and
defaulted receivables for each month to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Series&nbsp;20__-__,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">other series issued by the trust, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the depositor interest.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">These amounts will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__
based on the applicable investor percentage. Each investor percentage is calculated by reference to the invested amount or the adjusted
invested amount of the series. The &quot;investor percentages&quot; for Series&nbsp;20__-__ are:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the &quot;floating investor percentage,&quot; which equals (a)&nbsp;the adjusted
invested amount on the last day of the prior month (or, for the first month, the initial note balance of the series), divided by (b)&nbsp;the
adjusted pool balance as of the last day of the prior month (or, for the first month, the adjusted pool balance on ______, 20__), and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the &quot;fixed investor percentage,&quot; which equals (a)&nbsp;the invested
amount on the last day of the revolving period, divided by (b)&nbsp;the greater of (i)&nbsp;the adjusted pool balance on the last day
of the prior month, and (ii)&nbsp;the sum for all series of the adjusted invested amount for the prior month (for any series in its revolving
period) or the invested amount on the last day of the related revolving period (for any series not in its revolving period).</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I>For more information about how pool balance,
adjusted pool balance, invested amount and adjusted invested amount are determined, you should read &quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount
and Allocations &mdash; Required Pool Balance&quot; and &quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations &mdash; Investor Percentage
and Depositor Percentage.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The floating investor percentage is used for allocating
interest collections and defaulted receivables at any time and for allocating principal collections during the revolving period. The fixed
investor percentage is used for allocating principal collections during the [controlled accumulation period, ]required amortization period
or the early amortization period. Interest collections and principal collections are described in this prospectus in <I>&quot;Pool Balance,
Depositor Amount and Allocations &mdash; Allocation and Application of Collections.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_038"></A>[Optional Redemption</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The notes will be subject to an optional redemption,
in whole but not in part, at the option of the trust (a)&nbsp;on any payment date during the note redemption period without a make-whole
payment or (b)&nbsp;on any earlier payment date with a make-whole payment.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 84; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->83<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The servicer or the trust, or the administrator
on its behalf, will notify the indenture trustee and the rating agencies at least ten days before the payment date on which the option
is exercised. The trust will cause the depositors to deposit in the collection account on the business day before the payment date on
which the option is exercised (or, with the satisfaction of the rating agency condition, on that payment date) an amount sufficient to
pay the notes in full, including all accrued and unpaid interest, principal, any applicable make-whole payments[ or step-up amounts] due,
and all fees and expenses of the trust payable under the indenture supplement. The indenture trustee will notify the noteholders of the
redemption and provide instructions for surrender of the notes for final payment. Upon the exercise of the optional redemption, the notes
will be redeemed and paid in full.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_039"></A>[Make-Whole Payments</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">A make-whole payment
will be due on any principal payment made prior to the note redemption period due to the occurrence of the trust's exercise of its option
to redeem the notes on any payment date prior to the note redemption period. Make-whole payments </FONT>will not be paid on any class
of notes until all principal amounts payable on that payment date from interest collections have been paid in full. Any unpaid make-whole
payments on the notes will be payable in full on the final maturity date or any optional redemption date on which the notes are required
to be paid in full. Failure to pay make-whole payments on any notes on any payment date will not be an event of default until the final
maturity date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;make-whole payment&quot; for any principal
payment on a class of notes and a payment date will be an amount (not less than zero) equal to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>for the fixed rate notes, the excess of (a)&nbsp;the present value of (i)&nbsp;the amount of all future interest payments that would
otherwise accrue on the principal payment at the note interest rate for that class on such payment date until the [__] payment date prior
to the expected final payment date and (ii)&nbsp;the principal payment, discounted from the payment date on which such payment would have
been made to such payment date, monthly on a 30/360 basis at the sum of (A)&nbsp;(1)&nbsp;for the Class&nbsp;A-1 notes, [__]%, and (2)&nbsp;for
the Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D notes, [__]% plus (B)&nbsp;the higher of (1)&nbsp;zero and (2)&nbsp;the current maturity
matched U.S. Treasury rate over (b)&nbsp;the principal payment, and</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(2)</TD><TD>for the floating rate notes, the excess of (a)&nbsp;the present value of (i)&nbsp;the amount of all future interest payments that
would otherwise accrue on the principal payment at the note interest rate for that class on such payment date until the [__] payment date
prior to the expected final payment date and (ii)&nbsp;the principal payment, discounted from the payment date on which such payment would
have been made to such payment date, monthly on an actual/360 basis at the benchmark rate used to calculate the note interest rate for
that class and that payment date over (b)&nbsp;the principal payment.]</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_040"></A>Available Depositor Collections</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The depositor interest represents the interest
in the trust property not allocated to a series. The depositor amount generally represents the principal portion of the depositor interest
and must be equal to or greater than the required depositor amount. The &quot;required pool percentage&quot; for the Series&nbsp;20__-__
notes is [100]%.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I>For more information about how depositor amount
and required depositor amount are determined, you should read &quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations &mdash; Required Depositor
Amount.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A portion of the collections allocated to the depositor
interest, or &quot;available depositor collections,&quot; will be made available to make certain payments on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes
and other series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(5)</TD><TD>to the depositors.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Available depositor principal collections that
may be used for Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be limited to the available subordinated amount. If the available subordinated amount is zero,
available depositor collections allocated to the series will also be zero. If the amount of available depositor collections for a payment
date is insufficient to cover the aggregate shortfalls for all series, then available depositor collections will be allocated to each
series based on the ratio that its available subordinated amount bears to the aggregate available subordinated amount for all series that
have shortfalls.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">[&ldquo;Yield supplement interest collections&rdquo;
means, for the prior month for which the supplemental subordinated percentage is greater than zero, the lesser of (a)&nbsp;the product
of available depositor principal collections, times the floating investor percentage and (b)&nbsp;the product of the supplemental subordinated
percentage, times the excess of (i)&nbsp;the initial note balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ notes over (ii)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__
excess funding amount on that date, in each case, for that prior month.]</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_041"></A>Application of Investor Collections</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A portion of collections will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__
and deposited in the collection account each month for application as described below on the following payment date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&quot;Available investor interest collections&quot;
for Series&nbsp;20__-__ on a payment date will equal:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

prior month[ plus any yield supplement interest collections], plus</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">[on the earliest of the first payment date in the early amortization period,

account, plus]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the monthly depositor servicing fee, plus</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">[any available investor principal collections treated as available investor

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&quot;Available investor principal collections&quot;
for Series&nbsp;20__-__ on a payment date will equal the excess of:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">For each month during the revolving period, the
servicer will deposit available investor interest collections in the collection account in an amount necessary to cover the amounts described
in items (1)&nbsp;to (15) of <I>&quot;&mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I> below. In most cases, this amount will
equal the sum of the amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to (6). For each month during the [controlled accumulation period, ]required
amortization period or early amortization period, the servicer will deposit available investor principal collections in the collection
account until the amount in the collection account, together with amounts for Series&nbsp;20__-__ from the excess funding account, equals
the [controlled accumulation amount or the] adjusted invested amount.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

Interest, Fees and Other Items</I></B></FONT>. On each payment date, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to apply available
investor interest collections for the prior month for Series&nbsp;20__-__ in the following order:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>to the Class&nbsp;A noteholders, the interest due on [each class of][the] Class&nbsp;A notes for that payment date [or, if available
investor interest collections are insufficient to pay the interest in full, to each class of Class&nbsp;A notes pro rata based on the
note balance of the class],</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(2)</TD><TD>to the Class&nbsp;B noteholders, the interest due on the Class&nbsp;B notes for that payment date,</TD></TR></TABLE>

collections are paid.</P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->89<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If available investor interest collections for
a payment date are insufficient to cover the amounts above, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to apply funds from the following
sources on that payment date in the following order:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>from excess interest collections available from other series in excess interest sharing group one, to cover shortfalls of the amounts
described in items (1)&nbsp;to (16) above,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(2)</TD><TD>from available depositor collections (for available depositor principal collections, in an amount not to exceed the available subordinated
amount) to cover shortfalls of the amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to (10)&nbsp;above. If available depositor collections are insufficient
to reimburse the aggregate shortfalls for all series, then available depositor collections will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ based
on the ratio that its available subordinated amount bears to the aggregate available subordinated amounts for all series that have shortfalls.
If the amount of available depositor collections exceeds the aggregate shortfalls for all series, the excess available depositor collections
will be applied to cover amounts that the servicer fails to deposit in the excess funding account when it adjusts the principal balance
of a receivable as described in <I>&quot;Pool Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations &mdash; Excess Funding Account</I>.<I>&quot;</I>
The available subordinated amount will be reduced by the amount of available depositor principal collections applied to cover shortfalls
of the amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to (10)&nbsp;above,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">(3)</FONT></TD><TD>from the reserve account, to cover shortfalls of the amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to (7)&nbsp;above, and</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(4)</TD><TD>from available investor principal collections for that payment date, to cover shortfalls of the amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to
(4)&nbsp;above.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Payment of
Principal</I></B></FONT>. On each payment date, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to apply, first, the Series&nbsp;20__-__
excess funding amount and, second, available investor principal collections for Series&nbsp;20__-__ in the following order:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>if the payment date relates to the controlled accumulation period, to the principal funding account the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the
lesser of (i)&nbsp;the controlled accumulation amount (plus any shortfall in required deposits of the controlled accumulation amount for

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(2)</TD><TD>if the payment date relates to the required amortization period or the early amortization period, to the principal funding account
the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the adjusted invested amount, over (b)&nbsp;the amount deposited in the principal funding account from
the excess funding account, as described below,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(3)</TD><TD>to be treated as shared principal collections for other series in principal sharing group one, to be applied as described in <I>&quot;&mdash;
Groups &mdash; Principal Sharing Group One&quot;</I> and <I>&quot;&mdash; Principal Sharing Groups&quot;</I> below,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(4)</TD><TD>to the excess funding account, to increase the net adjusted pool balance to the required pool balance as described in <I>&quot;Pool
Balance, Depositor Amount and Allocations </I>&mdash; <I>Excess Funding Account,&quot;</I></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(5)</TD><TD>if the payment date relates to the excess funding period, to treat as available investor interest collections, to cover shortfalls
in the applications, payments and deposits under clauses (1)&nbsp;through (6)&nbsp;described in &quot;Application of Investor Collections

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(6)</TD><TD>to the holders of the depositor interest in the trust, all remaining available investor principal collections.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On each payment date that relates to the [controlled
accumulation period, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to deposit in the principal funding account from the excess funding
account the lesser of (a)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ excess funding amount, and (b)&nbsp;the lesser of (i)&nbsp;the controlled accumulation
amount, and (ii)&nbsp;the adjusted invested amount for that payment date. On each payment date that relates to the] required amortization
period or early amortization period, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to deposit in the principal funding account from the

for that payment date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If the Series&nbsp;20__-__ excess funding amount
and available investor principal collections for Series&nbsp;20__-__ for a payment date that relates to the [controlled accumulation period,
]required amortization period or an early amortization period are insufficient to cover the amount under item (1)&nbsp;above, the servicer
will direct the indenture trustee to apply available depositor collections (for available depositor principal collections, in an amount
not to exceed the available subordinated amount) on that payment date to cover the shortfall. If the amount of available depositor collections
is insufficient to cover the amount under item (1)&nbsp;above, as well as any similar shortfalls for other series, the available depositor
collections will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ based on the ratio that the available subordinated amount for Series&nbsp;20__-__
has to the aggregate &ldquo;available subordinated amounts&rdquo; for all series having the shortfall.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On the earlier of the expected final payment date
and the redemption date or on each payment date during the [controlled accumulation period, ]required amortization period or an early
amortization period, the servicer will direct the indenture trustee to apply amounts in the principal funding account in the following
order:</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>to the Class&nbsp;A noteholders, [pro rata based on the note balance of each class of Class&nbsp;A notes,] until the note balance

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(3)</TD><TD>to the Class&nbsp;C noteholders, until the note balance of the Class&nbsp;C notes is zero, and</TD></TR></TABLE>
