<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_042"></A>Defaulted Receivables and Principal Collections Used to Pay Interest</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The servicer will allocate to Series&nbsp;20__-__
the floating investor percentage of the principal balance of receivables that become defaulted receivables. The defaulted receivables
allocated to the series for a payment date will be funded from available investor interest collections, excess interest collections available
to the series from other series in excess interest sharing group one, available depositor collections and amounts in the reserve account,
as described in item (7)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I>
above. If the defaulted receivables allocated to the series for a payment date exceed the funds available from those sources, the available
subordinated amount (as reduced by the amount of available depositor principal collections applied to cover shortfalls of amounts described
in items (1)&nbsp;to (6)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I>
above), will be reallocated to the series to avoid a reduction of the invested amount and the available subordinated amount will be reduced
accordingly. Any remaining defaulted receivables allocated to the series will reduce the invested amount of the Class&nbsp;D notes, then
the Class&nbsp;C notes, then the Class&nbsp;B notes and finally the Class&nbsp;A notes[, pro rata based on the principal amount of each
class of Class&nbsp;A notes].</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">On a payment date, available investor principal
collections will be used to cover shortfalls in payments of interest on the notes in an amount not to exceed the sum of:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the available subordinated amount for that payment date, plus</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the invested amount of any class subordinated to the affected class for that
payment date.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The amount of principal collections used to pay
interest on the notes will reduce the available subordinated amount to zero, then the invested amount of the Class&nbsp;D notes, then
the Class&nbsp;C notes, and finally the Class&nbsp;B notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If principal collections are used to pay interest
on the notes, the available subordinated amount (as reduced by the amount of available depositor principal collections applied to reimburse
shortfalls of amounts described in items (1)&nbsp;to (10)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment
of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I> above) will be reallocated to the series to avoid a reduction of the invested amount.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Reductions in the invested amount from defaulted
receivables and principal collections used to pay interest on the notes may be reimbursed on later payment dates from available investor
interest collections, excess interest collections available from other series in excess interest sharing group one and available depositor
collections allocated to the series (for available depositor principal collections, in an amount not to exceed the available subordinated
amount), as described in items (9)&nbsp;and (10)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest,
Fees and Other Items&quot;</I> above. If the invested amount of the series is reduced to zero, the notes will not receive any further
allocations of interest collections or principal collections.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_043"></A>Ineligible Receivables and Overconcentration Amounts</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The depositors may sell ineligible receivables
to the trust so long as these ineligible receivables are originated in an eligible account. If ineligible receivables are in the trust,
the incremental subordinated amount will be increased to take into account the principal balance of the ineligible receivables allocated
to the series, which will result in a corresponding increase in the available subordinated amount.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The incremental subordinated amount will also be
increased by the aggregate principal balance of receivables that constitute overconcentrations allocated to the series, which will also
result in a corresponding increase in the available subordinated amount. The overconcentration amounts are calculated on each determination
date based on amounts on the last day of the prior month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in">&mdash;</TD><TD>the aggregate principal balance of receivables related to financed vehicles made by a single manufacturer (other than Ford or one

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_044"></A>Servicing Fees</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The share of the servicing fee and the back-up
servicing fee allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ for a payment date is the monthly servicing fee and the monthly back-up servicing fee.
The portion of the monthly servicing fee and the monthly back-up servicing fee that is attributable to the depositor interest is the &quot;monthly
depositor servicing fee,&quot; and that amount will be deducted from amounts otherwise payable to the depositors and deposited in the
collection account for each payment date.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;monthly servicing fee&quot; will equal
one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;__%, times (b)&nbsp;the percentage equal to (i)&nbsp;the floating investor percentage, divided
by (ii)&nbsp;the sum of the floating investor percentages for all series for that month, times (c)&nbsp;the pool balance on the last day
of the prior month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;monthly back-up servicing fee&quot; for
a month will equal one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;__%, times (b)&nbsp;the percentage equal to (i)&nbsp;the floating investor percentage,
divided by (ii)&nbsp;the sum of the floating investor percentages for all series for that month, times (c)&nbsp;the pool balance on the
last day of the prior month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;monthly depositor servicing fee&quot;
for a month will equal one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;the product of (i)&nbsp;the sum of __% and __%, times (ii)&nbsp;100% minus
the sum of the floating investor percentages for all series for that month, times (iii)&nbsp;the pool balance on the last day of the prior
month, times (b)&nbsp;the percentage equal to (i)&nbsp;the floating investor percentage, divided by (ii)&nbsp;the sum of the floating
investor percentages for all series that month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If the back-up servicer becomes the successor servicer,
amounts in a back-up servicer reserve account will be used to pay the transition expenses of the back-up servicer. Transition expenses
in excess of the amount in the back-up servicer reserve account will be paid from available investor interest collections as described
in item (15) of <I>&quot;</I>&mdash; <I>Application of Investor Collections &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot; </I>above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><I>For more information about the back-up servicer,
you should read &quot;Transaction Parties &mdash; Back-up Servicer.&quot;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_045"></A>Groups</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Excess Interest
Sharing Group One</I></B></FONT>. Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be included in a group of series referred to as &quot;excess interest sharing
group one.&quot; Excess interest collections for the series, as described in item (16) of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections
 &mdash; Payment of Interest, Fees and Other Items&quot;</I> above, will be made available to other series in excess interest sharing group
one whose share of interest collections is not sufficient to make required payments or deposits for that series. If available investor
interest collections for the series are insufficient to make all required payments and deposits, the series will have access to excess
interest collections from other series in excess interest sharing group one. Each series that is part of excess interest sharing group
one and has a shortfall will receive a share of the total amount of excess interest collections available for that month based on the
amount of shortfall for that series, divided by the total shortfall for all series in excess interest sharing group one for that month.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 96; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->95<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Principal Sharing
Group One</I></B></FONT>. Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be included in a group of series referred to as &quot;principal sharing group one.&quot;
Shared principal collections for the series, as described in item (2)&nbsp;of <I>&quot;&mdash; Application of Investor Collections &mdash;
Payment of Principal&quot;</I> above, will be made available to other series in principal sharing group one whose share of principal collections
is not sufficient to make required payments or deposits for that series. If available investor principal collections for the series (determined
without shared principal collections from other series) are insufficient to make all required payments and deposits, the series will have
access to shared principal collections from other series in principal sharing group one. Shared principal collections will be used to
reimburse principal shortfalls, but not to reimburse defaulted receivables allocated to the series. Each series that is part of principal
sharing group one and has a principal shortfall will receive a share of the total amount of shared principal collections available for
that month based on the amount of shortfall for that series, divided by the total shortfall for all series in principal sharing group
one for that month. To the extent that shared principal collections exceed principal shortfalls, the balance will be deposited in the
excess funding account if needed to increase the net adjusted pool balance to the required pool balance and then paid to the depositors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_046"></A>Amortization Events</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The &quot;amortization events&quot; for Series&nbsp;20__-__
consists of the following &quot;series amortization events&quot;:</P>

<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">(1)</TD><TD>either depositor fails (a)&nbsp;to make a payment or deposit within five business days of when the payment or deposit is required
to be made, or (b)&nbsp;to observe or perform in a material respect other covenants or agreements of the depositor in the related sale
and servicing agreement, the indenture or the Series&nbsp;20__-__ indenture supplement that adversely affects the amount or timing of
payments to be made to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders and continues for 60 days after it receives notice of the failure,</TD></TR></TABLE>

to be made to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders and which continues to be incorrect for 60 days after it receives notice of the failure,

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_047"></A>Events of Default and Acceleration</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The occurrence of any of the following will be
an &quot;event of default&quot; for the series under the indenture and the indenture supplement:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to pay interest due on any note which continues for 35 days,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to pay the principal of, [make-whole payments on, and any
accrued step-up amounts] on any note in full on its final maturity date,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust fails to observe or perform any covenant or agreement made in the
indenture, or a breach by the trust of a representation made in the indenture, which will cause an amortization event or an event of default
to occur, or adversely affect the amount or timing of payments to be made to the noteholders of any series or class, and the failure or
breach continues for 60 days after notice was given to the trust by the indenture trustee or to the trust and the indenture trustee by
at least 25% of the affected series, or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the bankruptcy or dissolution of the trust.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Failure to pay the principal of a note in full
on its expected final payment date is not an event of default. An event of default for one series will not necessarily be an event of
default for another series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Except in some limited circumstances, if a responsible
person of the indenture trustee knows of an event that with notice or lapse of time or both would become an event of default for a series,
it must notify all noteholders of the series within 90 days. If, for a series, a responsible person of the trust knows of an event that
with notice or lapse of time or both would become an event of default of the type described in the third item above, it must notify the
indenture trustee within five business days. If a responsible person</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 98; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->97<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">of the indenture trustee knows of an event of default for a series,
it must notify the noteholders of the series within five business days. The servicer must notify the trust, the back-up servicer, the
indenture trustee and each of the rating agencies within five business days of obtaining actual knowledge of an event of default.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A majority of a series may waive any event of default
for that series and its consequences except an event of default (a)&nbsp;in the payment of principal of or interest on any of the notes
(other than an event of default relating to failure to pay principal due only because of the acceleration of the notes) or (b)&nbsp;relating
to a covenant or agreement in the indenture that requires the unanimous consent of the noteholders of each affected series in order to
be modified.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Acceleration
of the Notes</I></B></FONT>. If an event of default occurs because of bankruptcy or dissolution of the trust, the notes of all series
will be accelerated automatically. If an event of default occurs for a series for another reason, the indenture trustee or a majority
of the series may accelerate the notes of that series and declare them to be immediately due and payable. Any acceleration of the notes
may, subject to the satisfaction of certain conditions, be rescinded by a majority of that series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">When a series is accelerated, an early amortization
period will start and principal and interest collections allocated to that series will be applied to make monthly principal and interest
payments on the notes of that series until the earlier of the date the notes are paid in full or the final maturity date of that series.
Funds in the collection account and excess funding account allocable to that series and other trust accounts for the series will be applied
to pay principal of and interest on that series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Remedies After
Acceleration</I></B></FONT>. If a series has been accelerated and the indenture trustee has not received any directions from the noteholders
about the time, method and place of conducting a proceeding for any remedy available to the indenture trustee, the indenture trustee may
continue to hold the trust property allocable to that series and apply collections on that trust property to make payments on those notes.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">If an event of default has occurred and the series
has been accelerated, the indenture trustee:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">may at its own election or at the direction of a majority of that series:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&mdash;</FONT></TD><TD>start a legal proceeding for the collection of the notes and enforce any judgment obtained,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">&mdash;</TD><TD>sell or liquidate any receivables at public or private sales,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in">&mdash;</TD><TD>exercise any remedies of a secured party under the UCC,</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&mdash;</FONT></TD><TD>take another action to protect and enforce the rights and remedies of the indenture trustee and the noteholders, or</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&mdash;</FONT></TD><TD>sell the trust property allocable to that series, but only if the indenture trustee determines that the proceeds of the sale will
be sufficient to pay the principal of and interest on the accelerated notes in full, and</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">must, at the direction of all of the holders of the series, cause the trust
to sell the portion of the trust property allocable to that series, regardless of the sufficiency of the proceeds from the sale to pay
the principal of and interest on the accelerated notes in full.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Following the sale of the trust property allocable
to the accelerated series and the application of the proceeds of that sale and of the amounts then held in the collection account and
the excess funding account allocable to that series and any trust accounts for that series and amounts available from enhancement for
that series, that series will no longer be entitled to any allocation of collections or other </P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 99; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->98<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">trust property under the indenture or the
indenture supplement, and those notes will no longer be outstanding.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Standard of
Care of the Indenture Trustee After an Event of Default</I></B></FONT>. If an event of default has occurred and is continuing, the indenture
trustee must exercise its rights and powers under the indenture using the same degree of care and skill that a prudent person would use
under the circumstances in conducting his or her own affairs. A majority of the affected series will have the right to direct the time,
method and place of conducting any proceeding for any remedy available to the indenture trustee after an event of default and acceleration
of the affected series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B><I>Limitation
on Legal Proceedings</I></B></FONT>. No noteholder will have the right to start any legal proceeding for any remedy under the indenture
or an indenture supplement described in <I>&quot;&mdash;Remedies After Acceleration&quot;</I> above unless:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the noteholder notified the indenture trustee of a continuing event of default,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">at least 25% of the affected series requested the indenture trustee to start
the legal proceeding,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the requesting noteholders offered reasonable security or indemnity satisfactory
to the indenture trustee against any liabilities that the indenture trustee may incur in complying with the request,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the indenture trustee failed to start the legal proceeding within 60 days
after its receipt of the notice, request and offer of indemnity, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a majority of the affected series has not given the indenture trustee any
inconsistent direction during the 60-day period.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A noteholder, however, has the right to start a
proceeding at any time to enforce its right to receive principal and interest due to it under its note, and that right may not be impaired
without the consent of the noteholder.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The indenture trustee and the noteholders of each
series and the other secured creditors of the trust will agree not to start or pursue a bankruptcy proceeding against the trust.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_048"></A>Satisfaction and Discharge of Indenture</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The indenture and the indenture supplement for
any series will not be discharged until:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the indenture trustee has received all notes of the series for cancellation
or, with certain limitations, funds sufficient to pay all notes of the series in full,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust has paid all amounts payable by it under the transaction documents,
and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the trust has delivered an officer's certificate and a legal opinion each
stating that all conditions to the satisfaction and discharge of the indenture and the indenture supplement for the series have been satisfied.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_049"></A>Amendments to Indenture and Indenture Supplement</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The indenture trustee and the trust may amend the
indenture or the indenture supplement for a series without the consent of the noteholders of any series for limited purposes, including
to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">further protect the indenture trustee's interest in the receivables and other
trust property subject to the lien of the indenture,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">add to the covenants of the trust for the benefit of the noteholders,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">transfer or pledge any additional property to the indenture trustee,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">correct any ambiguity, correct any mistake or add a term that is not inconsistent
with the other terms of the indenture or the indenture supplement, so long as the administrator certifies that the correction will not
cause an amortization event or an event of default to occur, or adversely affect the amount or timing of payments to be made to the noteholders
of any series or class, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">modify, eliminate or add terms required by or necessary to qualify the indenture
under the Trust Indenture Act.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The indenture trustee and the trust may amend the
indenture or the indenture supplement for a series to add, change or eliminate a term or modify the rights of all noteholders under the
indenture or the rights of noteholders of the related series under the indenture supplement:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">without the consent of the noteholders if (a)&nbsp;the administrator certifies
that the amendment will not cause an amortization event or an event of default to occur, or adversely affect the amount or timing of payments
to be made to the noteholders of any series or class and (b)&nbsp;the &quot;rating agency condition&quot; is satisfied for the rating
agencies for each series or the applicable series, which generally means, for any series and any proposed action, that each rating agency
rating that series either (i)&nbsp;confirms that the proposed action will not result in a reduction or withdrawal of its then-current
ratings of the notes of that series or (ii)&nbsp;within ten business days of receiving notice of the proposed action, does not notify
the depositors, the servicer, the owner trustee or the indenture trustee that the proposed action will result in a reduction or withdrawal
of its then-current ratings of the notes of that series, or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">with the consent of a majority of each series.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">In each case, the indenture trustee must receive a legal opinion that
for federal income tax purposes, the amendment will not cause any note to be deemed sold or exchanged or cause the trust to be treated
as an association or publicly traded partnership taxable as a corporation.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The prior consent of all adversely affected noteholders
of a series will be required for any amendment to the indenture or the indenture supplement that would:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">change the terms for amending the indenture or the indenture supplement or
voting or consent under the indenture or the indenture supplement,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">change the principal amount of or interest rate on any note of that series,
the expected final maturity date of the notes of that series, the priority of payments or how principal or interest payments are calculated
or made on the notes of that series,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">change the right of noteholders of that series to start legal proceedings
to enforce the indenture or the indenture supplement,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">change the calculation of the amount of a payment of principal of or interest
on any note, or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">permit the creation of a lien ranking prior or equal to, or impair, the lien
of the indenture trustee on the trust property.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_050"></A>Reopening of Series</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The trust may, without notice to or the consent
of, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ noteholders, issue additional notes of any class if:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

of the note balance of the junior class to the note balance of the more senior class is equal to or greater than the proportion that existed
on the closing date, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

the required pool balance.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_051"></A>New Issuances</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The depositors may cause the trust to issue a new
series under an indenture supplement without the consent of any noteholder of any series previously issued by the trust. Each series may
have different terms and enhancements from another series, including different expected final payment dates and series early amortization
events, which may cause some series to amortize earlier than others. The trust may offer a series under a prospectus, an offering memorandum
or in transactions either registered under the Securities Act or exempt from registration, directly, through one or more underwriters,
initial purchasers or placement agents, in fixed-price offerings or in negotiated transactions. The series may have different terms from
those described in this prospectus. If the trust has other series outstanding at the time it issues a new series, the prospectus, offering
memorandum or other disclosure document for the new series will list the main characteristics of those other series.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A new series may only be issued if, among other
things, the following conditions are satisfied:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">an indenture supplement specifying the principal terms of the new series is
delivered to the owner trustee and the indenture trustee,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the rating agency condition is satisfied for the rating agencies for each
series,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the depositors certify that the new issuance will not cause an amortization
event or an event of default to occur for any series, or materially and adversely affect the amount or timing of payments to be made to
the noteholders of any series,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the indenture trustee receives a legal opinion that for federal income tax
purposes, the new issuance will not cause the notes of any series to fail to qualify as debt or cause the trust to be treated as an association
or publicly traded partnership taxable as a corporation, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">after the new issuance, the net adjusted pool balance exceeds the required
pool balance.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_052"></A>Noteholder Communication</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A noteholder may communicate with the indenture
trustee and provide notices and make requests and demands and give directions to the indenture trustee as permitted by the transaction
documents through the procedures of DTC or by notice to the indenture trustee.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Three or more noteholders may request a list of
all noteholders of the trust maintained by the indenture trustee for the purpose of communicating with other noteholders about their rights
under the</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 102; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->101<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">indenture or under the notes. Any request must be accompanied by a copy of the communication that the requesting noteholders
propose to send.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">A noteholder may also send a request to the trust
or to the servicer, on behalf of the trust, stating that the noteholder is interested in communicating with other noteholders about the
possible exercise of rights under the transaction documents. The requesting noteholder must include in the request a description of the
method by which other noteholders may contact the requesting noteholder. The trust will promptly deliver any request to the servicer.
On receipt of a communication request, the servicer will include in the Form&nbsp;10-D filed in the next month the following information:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a statement that the trust received a communication request,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the date the request was received,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the name of the requesting noteholder,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a statement that the requesting noteholder is interested in communicating
with other noteholders about the possible exercise of rights under the transaction documents, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a description of the method by which the other noteholders may contact the
requesting noteholder.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Any expenses of the trust or the servicer relating
to an investor communication, including any review of documents evidencing ownership of a note and the inclusion of the investor communication
information in the Form&nbsp;10-D, will be paid by the servicer.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">In order to make a request or demand or to provide
notice to the trust, the owner trustee, the indenture trustee, the depositors, the sponsor or the servicer under the transaction documents,
a noteholder must either be a noteholder of record or must provide a written certification stating that it is a beneficial owner of a
note, together with supporting documentation such as a trade confirmation, an account statement, a letter from a broker or dealer verifying
ownership or another similar document evidencing ownership of a note.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><A NAME="ab_053"></A>Book-Entry Registration</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">The notes will be available only in book-entry
form except in the limited circumstances described below<I>. </I>All notes will be held in book-entry form by The Depository Trust Company,
or &quot;DTC,&quot; in the name of Cede&nbsp;&amp; Co., as nominee of DTC. Noteholders' interests in the notes will be represented through
financial institutions acting on their behalf as direct and indirect participants in DTC. Noteholders may hold their notes through DTC[,]
[or] Clearstream Banking Luxembourg S.A. [or Euroclear Bank S.A./N.V.], which will hold positions on behalf of their customers or participants
through their depositories, which in turn will hold positions in accounts as DTC participants. The notes will be traded as home market
instruments in both the U.S. domestic and European markets. Initial settlement and all secondary trades will settle in same-day funds.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Noteholders who hold their notes through DTC will
follow the settlement practices for U.S. corporate debt obligations. Noteholders who hold global notes through Clearstream [or Euroclear]
accounts will follow the settlement procedures for conventional eurobonds, except that there will be no temporary global notes and no
 &quot;lock-up&quot; or restricted period.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Actions of noteholders under the indenture will
be taken by DTC on instructions from its participants and all payments, notices, reports and statements to be delivered to noteholders
will be delivered to DTC or its nominee as the registered holder of the book-entry notes for distribution to holders of book-entry notes
according to DTC's rules&nbsp;and procedures.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 103; Value: 3 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->102<!-- Field: /Sequence --></P></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Prospective noteholders should review the rules&nbsp;and
procedures of DTC [,] [and] Clearstream [and Euroclear] for clearing, settlement, payments and tax withholding applicable to their purchase
of the notes. In particular, noteholders should note that DTC's rules&nbsp;and procedures limit the ability of the trust and the indenture
trustee to make post-payable adjustments for principal and interest payments after a period of time, which may be as short as 90 days.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.25in">Notes will be issued in physical form to noteholders
only if:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the administrator determines that DTC is no longer willing or able to properly
discharge its responsibilities as depository for the notes and the administrator or the depositors cannot appoint a qualified successor,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the administrator terminates the book-entry system through DTC, or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
