<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Form&nbsp;of
Notes</U>. Each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be in substantially the form of Exhibit&nbsp;A with variations required
or permitted by this Indenture Supplement and the Indenture. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes may have marks of identification and legends
or endorsements as determined by the Responsible Person of the Issuer executing the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes. The physical Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes will be produced by a method determined by the Responsible Person of the Issuer executing the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Book-Entry
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes initially will be issued as Book-Entry Notes. On or before the Series&nbsp;Issuance
Date, Global Notes representing each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be deposited with the Clearing Agency. [The Rule&nbsp;144A
Notes will be issued in the form of a restricted global note (the &quot;<U>Restricted Global Note</U>&quot;) and the Regulation S Notes
will be issued in the form of a temporary global note (the &quot;<U>Temporary Regulation S Global Note</U>&quot;) and a permanent global
note (the &quot;<U>Permanent Regulation S Global Note</U>&quot;), in each case, containing the applicable legends in Exhibit&nbsp;A.
Before the last day of the Distribution Compliance Period, beneficial interests in the Regulation S Notes will be represented by the
Temporary Regulation S Global Note, and on and after the last day of the Distribution Compliance Period, beneficial interests in the
Regulation S Notes will be represented by the Permanent Regulation S Global Note.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Denominations</U>.
The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, except for the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes, will be issued in minimum denominations of $1,000 and in multiples
of $1,000. The Rule&nbsp;144A Notes will be issued in minimum denominations of $100,000 and in multiples of $1,000 in excess of $100,000.
However, one Note of each Class&nbsp;may be issued in a different amount if it exceeds the minimum denomination for the Class.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(g)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Events
of Default</U>. The occurrence of the following event will be an additional Event of Default for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[the Issuer fails to pay the Make-Whole Payments on, and any Accrued Step-Up
Amounts on a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Note on the Final Maturity Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(h)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Final
Maturity Date</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be payable on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Trust
Termination Date</U>. The date on which the Issuer is scheduled to terminate under Section&nbsp;8.1(a)(i)&nbsp;of the Trust Agreement
will be the latest to occur of (i)&nbsp;the date stated in Section&nbsp;8.1(a)(i)&nbsp;of the Trust Agreement, (ii)&nbsp;December&nbsp;31
of the year in which the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date occurs and (iii)&nbsp;any later date stated in another Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(j)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Shelf-Eligible Series</U>. Series&nbsp;20__-__ is a Shelf-Eligible
Series.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(k)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>EEA-Eligible
Series</U>. Series&nbsp;20__-__ is [not] an EEA-Eligible Series.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;2.3.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Payments
on Notes</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Interest
Accrual</U>. Each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will accrue interest on its Note Balance for each Interest Period until the
Note Balance has been paid in full at a rate per annum equal to its Note Interest Rate for that Interest Period. [Interest on the Notes
[(other than</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 6; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->3<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
Floating Rate Notes)] will be calculated for each Interest Period on the basis of a 360-day year consisting of twelve 30-day months.]
[Interest on the Floating Rate Notes for each Interest Period will be calculated on the basis of the actual number of days in the Interest
Period and a 360-day year.] Interest on each Note for each Interest Period will be due and payable on the related Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Principal</U>.
If (i)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes remain Outstanding as of the Expected Final Payment Date or (ii)&nbsp;a Series&nbsp;20__-__
Amortization Event occurs before the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date, the principal of each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes will be payable in installments on each Payment Date during the Required Amortization Period or an Early Amortization Period, respectively
in each case, according to Section&nbsp;4.2(f). The Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be due and payable
on the earlier of the Redemption Date and the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date. The Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;of the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes will be due and payable on the date the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes are declared to be, or have automatically become, immediately
due and payable according to Section&nbsp;5.2(a)&nbsp;of the Indenture.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Step-Up
Amounts</U>. Following the Expected Final Payment Date, Step-Up Amounts will accrue on the Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;at the applicable
Step-Up Rate. Step-Up Amounts will be due and payable on each Payment Date. Step-Up Amounts on the Notes [(other than the Floating Rate
Notes)] will be computed on the basis of a 360-day year consisting of twelve 30-day months. [Step-Up Amounts on the Floating Rate Notes
will be computed on the basis of the actual number of days in the Interest Period and a 360-day year.]]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Make-Whole
Payments</U>. A Make-Whole Payment will be due on any repayment of the Note Balance made before the start of the Note Redemption Period
as a result of the occurrence of a Redemption Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Monthly Payment of Interest and Principal</U>. Payments of interest and principal on each
Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be made pro rata to the Registered Noteholders of that Class&nbsp;on each Payment Date.
For Book-Entry Notes, payments will be made by wire transfer to the account designated by the nominee of the Clearing Agency
according to Section&nbsp;2.10 of the Indenture. For Definitive Notes, payments will be made (i)&nbsp;if the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Noteholder has given to the Note Registrar instructions at least five Business Days before that Payment Date and the aggregate
original principal amount of the Noteholder's Notes is at least $1,000,000, by wire transfer to the account of the Registered
Noteholder or (ii)&nbsp;by check mailed first class mail, postage prepaid, to the Registered Noteholder's address as it appears on
the Note Register on the related Record Date. Amounts paid by wire transfers or checks that are undelivered will be held according
to Section&nbsp;3.3 of the Indenture.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Payment
of Final Installment</U>. The final installment of principal (whether payable by wire transfer or check) of each Series&nbsp;20__-__
Note on a Payment Date, the Redemption Date or the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date will be payable only on presentation and surrender
of the Note. The Indenture Trustee will notify each Registered Noteholder of the date the Issuer expects to pay the final installment
on the Notes, which notice will be delivered no later than five days before that date, and the place where the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes
may be presented and surrendered for payment.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;2.4.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Additional
Issuance; Reopening</U>. The Issuer may from time to time, without notice to, or the consent of, the Noteholders of any Series, create
and issue additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes of the same Class&nbsp;as any Class&nbsp;issued on the Closing Date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will form part of and have the same Principal Terms as the previously issued Class, except for (i)&nbsp;the
initial principal amount of that Class, the Initial Invested Amount and the initial Note Balance of that Class&nbsp;on the Closing Date,
(ii)&nbsp;the accrual and payment of interest before the issuance date of the additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, and (iii)&nbsp;the
first payment of interest following the issuance of the additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes.&nbsp;&nbsp;When issued, the additional
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be equally and ratably entitled to the benefits of the Indenture and this Indenture Supplement applying
to those Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes of the same Class&nbsp;issued on the Closing Date without preference, priority or distinction.&nbsp;&nbsp;The
obligation of the Indenture Trustee to authenticate and deliver additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes after the Closing Date and to execute
and deliver any amendments to this Indenture Supplement to facilitate the additional issuance will be subject to the satisfaction of
the following conditions:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Rating
Agency Notice</U>. On or before the second Business Day before the issuance of the additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, the Issuer has
given the Indenture Trustee and each Rating Agency notice of the additional issuance and the date of the additional issuance;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Delivery
of Amendments</U>. The Issuer has delivered to the Indenture Trustee any amendments to this Indenture Supplement required to facilitate
the additional issuance, in form reasonably satisfactory to the Indenture Trustee executed by the Issuer;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Rating
Agency Condition</U>. The Rating Agency Condition has been satisfied for the additional issuance;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Officer's
Certificate of Depositor</U>. Each Depositor has delivered to the Indenture Trustee an Officer's Certificate, dated the date of the additional
issuance, stating that:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
additional issuance will not have an Adverse Effect or cause an Amortization Event to occur for any Series; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;all
conditions under this Section&nbsp;2.4 to the issuance of the additional Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes have been met;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Subordination</U>.
On or before the additional issuance date for any Class&nbsp;[(treating the Class&nbsp;A-1 and Class&nbsp;A-2 Notes as a single Class)],
the Issuer will have issued Notes of each Class&nbsp;that is junior to that Class&nbsp;needed for the proportion of the Note Principal
Balance of each junior Class&nbsp;to the Note Principal Balance of any more senior Class&nbsp;is equal to or greater than the proportion
that existed on the Closing Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__
Reserve Account</U>. The Depositors have deposited in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account from the proceeds of the issuance the amount
as is necessary to cause the amount on deposit to equal the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Required Amount after giving effect to
the issuance; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->5<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(g)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Required Pool Balance</U>. The Net Adjusted Pool Balance equals or exceeds the Required Pool Balance after
giving effect to the additional issuance (taking into account any deposit of the proceeds of the additional Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes in the Excess Funding Account).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;2.5.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[Yield
Supplement Interest Collections. At the direction of the Depositors, the Issuer may from time to time, without notice to, or the consent
of, the Noteholders of any Series, (a)&nbsp;increase the Subordinated Percentage for Series&nbsp;20__-__ for a Determination Date and
the related Collection Period by a specified percentage (the &quot;<U>Supplemental Subordinated Percentage</U>&quot;) not to exceed ____%
in the aggregate or (b)&nbsp;decrease the Supplemental Subordinated Percentage for Series&nbsp;20__-__ for a Determination Date and the
related Collection Period, but not less than zero. If the Supplemental Subordinated Percentage is greater than zero for a Determination
Date, a portion of the Available Depositor Principal Collections allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__ for the related Collection Period in
an amount equal to the Yield Supplement Interest Collections will be treated as Interest Collections and included in the Investor Interest
Collections for that Collection Period.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;III<BR>
REPORTS AND Servicing</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;3.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Reports
and Statements to Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Monthly Investor Report</U>. At least two Business Days before each Payment Date, the Servicer will
deliver to the Depositors, the Issuer, the Indenture Trustee, the Note Paying Agent, the Administrator and the Rating Agencies a
servicing report substantially in the form of Exhibit&nbsp;B (the &quot;<U>Monthly Investor Report</U>&quot;) for that Payment Date
and the related Collection Period. A Responsible Person of the Servicer will certify that the information in the Monthly Investor
Report is accurate in all material respects.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Delivery
to Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders</U>. On each Payment Date, the Indenture Trustee will deliver the Monthly Investor Report to each
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder of record as of the most recent Record Date (which delivery may be made by e-mail to the e-mail addresses
in the Note Register without need for confirmation of receipt or by making the report available to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders
through the Indenture Trustee's website, which initially is located at ________________________).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Benchmark
Replacement; Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes</U>. Upon receipt of notice from the Issuer of the determination of a Benchmark
Replacement and/or the making of any Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes, the Servicer will include in the Monthly Investor Report
any information regarding the Unadjusted Benchmark Replacement, the Benchmark Replacement Adjustment and any such Benchmark Replacement
Conforming Changes provided by the Issuer.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Tax
Information</U>. Starting in the year after the Closing Date, the Indenture Trustee will deliver or cause to be delivered to each Person
who at any time during the prior calendar year was a Noteholder of record, a statement containing the information required to be given
to a noteholder by an issuer of indebtedness, in the form and at the time required under the Code.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;3.2.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Servicing
Compensation</U>. The share of the Servicing Fee allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__ for a Payment Date is equal to the Monthly Servicing
Fee. The portion of the Servicing Fee that is not allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be paid by the holders of the Depositor Interest
or the Noteholders of other Series&nbsp;(under the related Indenture Supplement). The Issuer, the Indenture Trustee or the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Noteholders will not be liable for the share of the Servicing Fee to be paid by the holders of the Depositor Interest or the Noteholders
of any other Series.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;IV<BR>
Rights of SERIES 20__-__ Noteholders<BR>
and Allocation and Application of Collections</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Collections
and Allocations</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Allocations</U>. Under Section&nbsp;8.4(a)&nbsp;of the
Indenture,&nbsp;Interest Collections, Principal Collections and Defaulted Receivables will be allocated between Series&nbsp;20__-__
and the Depositor Interest and then applied to Series&nbsp;20__-__ and the Depositor Interest under this Article&nbsp;IV.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Allocations
to Depositor Interest</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Available
Depositor Collections</U>. On each Deposit Date, the Servicer will make the following deposits and payments from Available Depositor
Collections for that Deposit Date or the related Collection Period, as applicable, in the following order of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(A)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[to
                                            the Collection Account, an amount equal to the Yield Supplement Interest Collections for
                                            Series&nbsp;20__-__ and each other Series;]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(B)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">to
                                            the Collection Account, but only if needed to pay, to the knowledge of the Servicer on that
                                            Deposit Date, the following amounts on the related Payment Date: (I)&nbsp;to cover shortfalls
                                            in payments and deposits required to be made from Available Investor Interest Collections
                                            on the related Payment Date under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(ii), and to cover similar shortfalls
                                            for other Series, and (II)&nbsp;during the Required Amortization Period or an Early Amortization
                                            Period, to cover amounts to be deposited under Section&nbsp;4.2(e)&nbsp;on that Payment Date;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(C)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">to
                                            the Excess Funding Account, if the Required Depositor Amount for the prior Calculation Date
                                            (and, if that Calculation Date is a Determination Date, after giving effect to the allocations,
                                            payments, withdrawals and deposits to be made on the Payment Date following that Determination
                                            Date) exceeds the Depositor Amount; and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(D)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(I)&nbsp;if
                                            the Depositors are the sole holders of the Depositor Interest, to the Depositors according
                                            to their respective percentage interests in the Depositor Interest or (II)&nbsp;otherwise,
                                            to the Depositor Interest Account</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Excess
Depositor Interest Collections</U>. On each Deposit Date, the Servicer will make the following deposits and payments from Excess Depositor
Interest Collections for that Deposit Date or the related Collection Period, as applicable, in the following order of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(A)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">to
                                            the Collection Account, until the amount deposited under this clause (A)&nbsp;is equal to
                                            the Monthly Depositor Servicing Fee for all Series&nbsp;for that Collection Period; and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(B)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(I)&nbsp;if
                                            the Depositors are the sole holders of the Depositor Interest, to the Depositors according
                                            to their respective percentage interests in the Depositor Interest or (II)&nbsp;otherwise,
                                            to the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest
                                            according to the Trust Agreement, any remaining amount.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Depositor Principal Collections</U>. On each Deposit Date, the Servicer will make the following deposits and payments from Excess Depositor
Principal Collections for that Deposit Date or the related Collection Period, as applicable, in the following order of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">

                                            the Excess Funding Account, if the Required Depositor Amount for the prior Calculation Date
                                            (and, if that Calculation Date is a Determination Date, after giving effect to the allocations,
                                            payments, withdrawals and deposits to be made on the Payment Date following that Determination
                                            Date) exceeds the Depositor Amount;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 1.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(B)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">to
                                            the Collection Account, until the amount deposited under this clause (B)&nbsp;is equal to
                                            the excess, if any, of (I)&nbsp;the Monthly Depositor Servicing Fee for all Series&nbsp;for
                                            that Collection Period <U>over</U> (II)&nbsp;the amount deposited in the Collection Account
                                            under Section&nbsp;4.1(b)(ii)(A); and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

                                            the Depositors are the sole holders of the Depositor Interest, to the Depositors according
                                            to their respective percentage interests in the Depositor Interest or (II)&nbsp;otherwise,
                                            to the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest
                                            according to the Trust Agreement, any remaining amount.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Available
Depositor Collections True-up</U>. On each Determination Date, the Servicer will deposit in the Collection Account the lesser of (A)&nbsp;the
portion, if any, of the amount stated in Section&nbsp;4.1(b)(i)(A)(I)&nbsp;for the related Collection Period that has not previously
been deposited in the Collection Account under Section&nbsp;4.1(b)(i)(A)(I), and (B)&nbsp;the aggregate amount paid to the Depositors
or to the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest for the related Collection Period under
Section&nbsp;4.1(b)(i)(C). Any amount deposited under this Section&nbsp;4.1(b)(iv)&nbsp;will be repaid</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">to
the Servicer by the holders of the Depositor Interest or, if not so repaid, may be withheld by the Servicer from later distributions
to the holders of the Depositor Interest.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Allocations
to Series&nbsp;20__-__</U>. The Servicer will allocate to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders and deposit in the Collection Account for
application under this Indenture Supplement the following amounts:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
each Deposit Date, an amount equal to the Investor Interest Collections for that Deposit Date or the related Collection Period, as applicable,
until the amount in the Collection Account allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ equals the excess of (A)&nbsp;the amounts to be paid or distributed,
to the knowledge of the Servicer on that Deposit Date, on the related Payment Date under Section&nbsp;4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (xvi), <U>over
</U>(B)&nbsp;the Monthly Depositor Servicing Fee for the related Collection Period;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
each Deposit Date, an amount equal to the Investor Principal Collections for that Deposit Date or the related Collection Period, as applicable,
until the amount in the Collection Account allocated to Series&nbsp;__-_ equals the amounts to be paid or distributed, to the knowledge
of the Servicer on that Deposit Date, on the related Payment Date under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(iv), (c)&nbsp;or (d), as applicable;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
each Determination Date, an amount equal to the lesser of (A)&nbsp;the portion, if any, of the excess of (I)&nbsp;the amounts to be paid
or distributed on the related Payment Date under Section&nbsp;4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (xvi), <U>over</U> (II)&nbsp;the Monthly Depositor
Servicing Fee for the related Collection Period that has not previously been deposited in the Collection Account under Section&nbsp;4.1(c)(i),
and (B)&nbsp;the amount of Investor Interest Collections for the related Collection Period that has not previously been deposited in
the Collection Account under Section&nbsp;4.1(c)(i); and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
each Determination Date, an amount equal to the lesser of (A)&nbsp;the portion, if any, of the amounts to be paid or distributed on the
related Payment Date under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(iv), (c)&nbsp;or (d), as applicable, that has not previously been deposited in the Collection
Account under Section&nbsp;4.1(c)(ii), and (B)&nbsp;the amount of Investor Principal Collections for the related Collection Period that
has not previously been deposited in the Collection Account under Section&nbsp;4.1(c)(ii).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.2.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Application of Available Funds in Collection Account and Other Sources</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Available
Investor Interest Collections</U>. If the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly Investor Report by the related Determination Date,
the Indenture Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) will, on each Payment Date and to the extent of Available
Investor Interest Collections in the Collection Account, make the following applications, payments or deposits in the following order
of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Noteholders of [the][each Class&nbsp;of] Class&nbsp;A Notes, the Accrued Note Interest for [the][each Class&nbsp;of] Class&nbsp;A
Notes for that Payment Date [or, if Available Investor Interest Collections are insufficient to pay the Accrued Note Interest in full
for each Class&nbsp;of Class&nbsp;A Notes, to the Noteholders of each Class&nbsp;of Class&nbsp;A Notes, pro rata, based on the Note Balance
of each Class&nbsp;of Class&nbsp;A Notes];</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Noteholders of the Class&nbsp;B Notes, the Accrued Note Interest for the Class&nbsp;B Notes for that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Noteholders of the Class&nbsp;C Notes, the Accrued Note Interest for the Class&nbsp;C Notes for that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;to the Noteholders of the Class&nbsp;D Notes, the Accrued Note Interest for the Class&nbsp;D Notes for that Payment
Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(v)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;pro
rata, to the payment of all amounts, including indemnities, then due to the Owner Trustee, the Indenture Trustee and the Asset Representations
Reviewer for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, and, to or at the direction of the Issuer, any expenses incurred by the Issuer for the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes according to the Transaction Documents, in each case, if not paid by the Servicer or the Administrator, up to a maximum of $________
per year;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(vi)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;pro
rata (A)&nbsp;to the Back-up Servicer, the Monthly Back-up Servicing Fee for that Payment Date, if any, together with any Monthly Back-up
Servicing Fees previously due but not paid on prior Payment Dates, and (B)&nbsp;if Ford Credit or one of its Affiliates is no longer
the Servicer, to the Servicer, the Monthly Servicing Fee for that Payment Date, together with any Monthly Servicing Fees previously due
but not paid on prior Payment Dates (unless the amount has been netted against deposits in the Collection Account according to Section&nbsp;8.4(c)&nbsp;of
the Indenture);</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(vii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
treat as Available Investor Principal Collections for that Payment Date, the Investor Default Amount for that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(viii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Deposit Amount for that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ix)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
treat as Available Investor Principal Collections for that Payment Date, the sum of Investor Charge-Offs that have not been previously
reimbursed;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(x)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
treat as Available Investor Principal Collections for that Payment Date, the sum of Reallocated Principal Collections that have not been
previously reimbursed;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xi)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[starting
on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Funding Date, to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account,
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Deposit Amount for that Payment Date;]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;if
Ford Credit is the Servicer, to the Servicer, the Monthly Servicing Fee for that Payment Date, together with any Monthly Servicing Fees
previously due but not paid on prior Payment Dates (unless the amount has been netted against deposits in the Collection Account according
to Section&nbsp;8.4(c)&nbsp;of the Indenture);</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest according to the Trust Agreement to increase
the Available Subordinated Amount, the excess of the Required Subordinated Amount <U>over</U> the</FONT></P>

the Noteholders, any Make-Whole Payments due on the Notes and, after the Expected Final Payment Date, to the Noteholders, any Accrued
Step-Up Amounts due on the Notes, payable sequentially by Class&nbsp;and pro rata to each Class&nbsp;based on the amount due;]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
pro rata, to the payment of all amounts, including indemnities, then due to the Owner Trustee, the Indenture Trustee and the Asset
Representations Reviewer for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, and any expenses incurred by the Issuer for the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes according to the Transaction Documents, in each case, if not paid by the Servicer or the Administrator or under clause
(v)&nbsp;above;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xvi)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Back-up Servicer, any amounts due under Section&nbsp;2.3(b)&nbsp;of the Back-up Servicing Agreement and any Transition Costs due
under Section&nbsp;2.3(c)&nbsp;of the Back-up Servicing Agreement in excess of the amount in the Back-up Servicer Reserve Account, in
each case, for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xvii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
treat as Excess Interest Collections available from Series&nbsp;20__-__, the Interest Collections Shortfalls for other Series&nbsp;in
Excess Interest Sharing Group One; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(xviii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest according to the Trust Agreement, all remaining
Available Investor Interest Collections.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Application
of Credit Enhancement</U>. If Available Investor Interest Collections for any Payment Date are insufficient to make the applications,
payments and deposits required under Section&nbsp;4.2(a), and if the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly Investor Report by the
related Determination Date, the Indenture Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) will, on or before that Payment
Date, apply available funds from the following sources in the following order of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;from
Excess Interest Collections available from other Series&nbsp;in Excess Interest Sharing Group One, to cover shortfalls in the applications,
payments and deposits under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (xvi)&nbsp;in that order;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;from
Available Depositor Interest Collections and Available Depositor Principal Collections (for Available Depositor Principal Collections,
in an amount not exceeding the Available Subordinated Amount (before giving effect to Section&nbsp;4.3) for that Payment Date), to cover
shortfalls in the applications, payments and deposits required under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (x)&nbsp;in that order. If the amount
of Available Depositor Collections is insufficient to cover those shortfalls for Series&nbsp;20__-__, as well as any similar shortfalls
for other Series, then Available Depositor Collections will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ based on the ratio that the Available
Subordinated Amount for Series&nbsp;20__-__ has to the aggregate &quot;Available Subordinated Amounts&quot; for all Series&nbsp;having
those shortfalls. If the amount of Available Depositor Collections exceeds the</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>
