<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">aggregate
amount of those shortfalls for all Series, then the excess Available Depositor Collections will be applied to cover any unpaid Adjustment
Payments;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;from
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Available Amount, to cover shortfalls in the applications, payments and deposits required under
Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (vii)&nbsp;in that order; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;from
the Reallocated Principal Collections for that Payment Date, to cover shortfalls in the payments required under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through
(iv).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Available
Investor Principal Collections</U>. If the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly Investor Report by the related Determination Date,
the Indenture Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) will, on each Payment Date and if Available Investor
Principal Collections on deposit in the Collection Account, make the following applications, payments or deposits in the following order
of priority:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
any Payment Date for the [Controlled Accumulation Period,] Required Amortization Period or an Early Amortization Period, to the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Principal Funding Account, the excess, if any, of the Monthly Principal Amount for that Payment Date <U>over</U> the amount deposited
in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account from the Excess Funding Account under Section&nbsp;4.2(d)&nbsp;on that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
other Principal Sharing Series&nbsp;in Principal Sharing Group One, the Shared Principal Collections for that Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Excess Funding Account, the excess, if any, of the Required Pool Balance <U>over</U> the Net Adjusted Pool Balance under Section&nbsp;8.3(b)(ii)&nbsp;of
the Indenture; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;on
any Payment Date during the Excess Funding Period, to treat as Available Investor Interest Collections for that Payment Date, to cover
shortfalls in the applications, payments and deposits under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (vi)&nbsp;in that order; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(v)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;to
the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest according to the Trust Agreement, all remaining
Available Investor Principal Collections.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Excess
Funding Amounts</U>. If the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly Investor Report by the related Determination Date, the Indenture
Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) will, on each Payment Date for the [Controlled Accumulation Period,]
Required Amortization Period or an Early Amortization Period, deposit in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account from the Excess
Funding Account the lesser of (i)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Excess Funding Amount, and (ii)&nbsp;the Monthly Principal Amount for
that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Insufficient
Available Investor Principal Collections</U>. If Available Investor Principal Collections for any Payment Date for the Required Amortization
Period or an Early</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 15; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->12<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Amortization
Period are insufficient to deposit the amount required under Section&nbsp;4.2(c)(i), and if the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly
Investor Report by the related Determination Date, the Indenture Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) will,
on that Payment Date and after giving effect to Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(ii), deposit in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account
Available Depositor Interest Collections and remaining Available Depositor Principal Collections (for Available Depositor Principal Collections,
in an amount not to exceed the Available Subordinated Amount) on that Payment Date in an amount equal to the excess of the Adjusted Invested
Amount <U>over</U> the sum of the amounts deposited in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account from Available Investor Principal
Collections under Section&nbsp;4.2(c)(i)&nbsp;and from the Excess Funding Account under Section&nbsp;4.2(d). If the amount of Available
Depositor Collections is insufficient to cover the amount required under Section&nbsp;4.2(c)(i)&nbsp;for Series&nbsp;20__-__, as well
as any similar shortfalls for other Series, then Available Depositor Collections will be allocated to Series&nbsp;20__-__ based on the
ratio that the Available Subordinated Amount for Series&nbsp;20__-__ has to the aggregate &quot;Available Subordinated Amounts&quot;
for all Series&nbsp;having those shortfalls.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Payments
of Principal</U>. If an Early Amortization Period has not begun, on the earlier of (i)&nbsp;the Expected Final Payment Date or (ii)&nbsp;the
Redemption Date, or on each Payment Date for the Required Amortization Period or an Early Amortization Period, and if the Indenture Trustee
has received the Monthly Investor Report by the related Determination Date, the Indenture Trustee (based on the information in the Monthly
Investor Report) will withdraw an amount up to the aggregate Note Balance of Series&nbsp;20__-__ from the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal
Funding Account for payment in the following order of priority: (i)&nbsp;to the Noteholders of [the][each Class&nbsp;of] Class&nbsp;A
Notes, [pro rata based on the principal amount of each Class&nbsp;of Class&nbsp;A Notes,] until the Note Balance of [the][each Class&nbsp;of]
Class&nbsp;A Notes is reduced to zero, (ii)&nbsp;to the Noteholders of Class&nbsp;B Notes, until the Note Balance of the Class&nbsp;B
Notes is reduced to zero, (iii)&nbsp;to the Noteholders of the Class&nbsp;C Notes, until the Note Balance of the Class&nbsp;C Notes is
reduced to zero and (iv)&nbsp;to the Noteholders of the Class&nbsp;D Notes, until the Note Balance of the Class&nbsp;D Notes is reduced
to zero.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(g)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[<U>Controlled
Accumulation Period</U>. The Controlled Accumulation Period is scheduled to start on the first day of the ________ 20__ Collection Period.
However, if the Accumulation Period Length is less than six Collection Periods, the date the Controlled Accumulation Period actually
starts will be delayed to the first day of the Collection Period that is the number of Collection Periods before the Expected Final Payment
Date at least equal to the Accumulation Period Length. On or before each Determination Date starting with the Determination Date in the
_________ 20__ Collection Period and ending when the Controlled Accumulation Period starts, the Servicer will determine the &quot;Accumulation
Period Length.&quot;]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.3.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Investor
Charge-Offs</U>. On each Determination Date, the Servicer will calculate the Investor Default Amount, if any, for the related Payment
Date. If the Investor Default Amount for any Payment Date exceeds the sum of the amounts applied to fund the Investor Default Amount
under Section&nbsp;4.2(a)(vii)&nbsp;(including any amounts applied under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)), then the excess will be applied in the
following order of priority to reduce (a)&nbsp;the Available Subordinated Amount for the related Determination Date (after giving effect
to any reductions of the Available Subordinated Amount under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(ii)), (b)&nbsp;the Class&nbsp;D</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 16; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->13<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Invested
Amount, (c)&nbsp;the Class&nbsp;C Invested Amount, (d)&nbsp;the Class&nbsp;B Invested Amount, and (e)&nbsp;the remaining Invested Amount.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.4.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Reallocated Principal Collections</U>. On each Payment Date, the Reallocated Principal
Collections for that Payment Date will be applied in the following order of priority to reduce (a)&nbsp;the Available Subordinated
Amount (after giving effect to any reductions of the Available Subordinated Amount under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(ii)&nbsp;and
Section&nbsp;4.3), (b)&nbsp;the Class&nbsp;D Invested Amount, (c)&nbsp;the Class&nbsp;C Invested Amount, and (d)&nbsp;the
Class&nbsp;B Invested Amount.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.5.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Excess Interest Collections</U>. On each Payment Date, Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be allocated an
amount equal to the product of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate amount of Excess Interest Collections for all Excess Interest Sharing
Series&nbsp;in Excess Interest Sharing Group One for that Payment Date, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;a fraction with a numerator equal to
the Interest Collections Shortfall for Series&nbsp;20__-__ for that Payment Date and a denominator equal to the aggregate amount of
Interest Collections Shortfalls for all Excess Interest Sharing Series&nbsp;in Excess Interest Sharing Group One for that Payment
Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.6.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Shared Principal Collections</U>. On each Payment Date, Series&nbsp;20__-__ will be allocated an
amount equal to the product of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate amount of Shared Principal Collections for all Principal Sharing
Series&nbsp;in Principal Sharing Group One for that Payment Date, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;a fraction with a numerator equal to the
Principal Shortfall for Series&nbsp;20__-__ for that Payment Date and a denominator equal to the aggregate amount of Principal
Shortfalls for all Principal Sharing Series&nbsp;in Principal Sharing Group One for that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.7.&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Establishment

Funding Account</U>&quot; with account number ______;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[&quot;<U>Accumulation

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Control</U>.
Each of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts will be under the control of the Indenture Trustee so long as the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts
remain subject to the Lien of this Indenture Supplement, except that the Servicer may make deposits to and direct the Indenture Trustee
to make deposits to or withdrawals from the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts according to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Documents.
Following the payment in full of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes and the release of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts from the Lien of this
Indenture Supplement, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts will be under the control of the Issuer.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Benefit
of Accounts; Deposits and Withdrawals</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts and all cash, money, securities, investments, financial assets
and other property deposited in or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->14<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">credited
to them will be held by the Indenture Trustee as secured party for the benefit of the 20__-__ Secured Parties and, after payment in full
of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes and the release of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts from the Lien of this Indenture Supplement, as agent
of the Issuer and as part of the Trust Property. All deposits to and withdrawals from the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts will be made according
to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Documents.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Maintenance
of Accounts</U>. If an institution maintaining the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts ceases to be a Qualified Institution, the Servicer will,
with the Indenture Trustee's assistance as necessary, move the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts to a Qualified Institution within 30 days.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Compliance</U>. Each Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account will be subject to the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account Control Agreement. The Servicer will ensure that the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account Control Agreement
requires the Qualified Institution maintaining the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts to comply with &quot;entitlement orders&quot; (as
defined in Section&nbsp;8-102 of the UCC) from the Indenture Trustee without further consent of the Issuer, if the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes are Outstanding, and to act as a &quot;securities intermediary&quot; according to the UCC.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Excess
to Holders of Depositor Interest</U>. If on any Payment Date, after giving effect to all withdrawals from and deposits in the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accounts, the amount in any Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account exceeds the amount required to be in that Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account under this
Indenture Supplement or any other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Document, then the Indenture Trustee will, at the direction of the
Servicer, distribute the excess to the Depositor Interest Account for distribution to the holders of the Depositor Interest according
to the Trust Agreement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.8.&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Investment of Funds in Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Permitted
Investments</U>. If no Default or Event of Default has occurred and is continuing, the Servicer may instruct the Indenture Trustee to
invest any funds in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts in Permitted Investments, and, if investment instructions are received, the Indenture
Trustee will direct the Qualified Institution maintaining the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts to invest the funds in the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accounts in those Permitted Investments. The investment instructions from the Servicer may be in the form of a standing instruction.
If (i)&nbsp;the Servicer fails to give investment instructions for any funds in a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account to the Indenture Trustee
by 11:00 a.m.&nbsp;New York time (or other time as may be agreed by the Indenture Trustee) on the Business Day before a Payment Date
or (ii)&nbsp;the Qualified Institution receives notice from the Indenture Trustee that a Default or Event of Default has occurred and
is continuing for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, the Qualified Institution will invest and reinvest funds in the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accounts according to the last investment instructions received, if any. If no prior investment instructions have been received or if
the instructed investments are no longer available or permitted, the Indenture Trustee will notify the Servicer and request new investment
instructions, and the funds will remain uninvested until new investment instructions are received. The Servicer may direct the Indenture
Trustee to consent, vote, waive or take any other action, or not to take any action, on any matters available to the holder of the Permitted
Investments.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 18; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->15<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Maturity
of Investments</U>. Any Permitted Investments of funds in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts (or any reinvestments of the Permitted Investments)
for a Collection Period must mature, if applicable, and be available no later than the related Payment Date. However, funds in the Reserve
Account may be invested in Permitted Investments that will not mature or be available before the related Payment Date if the Rating Agency
Condition has been satisfied for the investment. Any Permitted Investments with a maturity date will be held to their maturity, except
that such Permitted Investments may be sold or disposed of before their maturity (i)&nbsp;if they relate to funds in the Reserve Account
required to make payments under Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(iii)&nbsp;or (ii)&nbsp;in connection with the sale or liquidation of the Collateral
following an Event of Default under Section&nbsp;5.6 of the Indenture.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>No
Liability for Investments</U>. None of the Depositors, the Servicer, the Indenture Trustee or the Qualified Institution maintaining any
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account will be liable for the selection of Permitted Investments or for investment losses incurred on Permitted
Investments (other than in the capacity as obligor, if applicable).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Continuation
of Liens in Investments</U>. The Servicer will not direct the Indenture Trustee to make any investment of any funds or to sell any investment
held in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Account unless the security interest Granted and perfected in the account in favor of the Indenture Trustee
will continue to be perfected in the investment or the proceeds of the sale, in each case, without any further action by any Person.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.9.&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Initial
Reserve Account Deposit</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account will be funded by the Depositors on the Closing Date in the amount
equal to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Required Amount for that date and will be increased and decreased as stated in this
Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Reserve
Account Step-Up Deposit</U>. On or before the first day of any Subordination Step-Up Period, the Depositors may elect to increase the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Required Percentage for that Subordination Step-Up Period instead of increasing the Subordination
Factor, by (i)&nbsp;notifying the Servicer and the Indenture Trustee of the election and (ii)&nbsp;depositing the amount of the related
increase of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Required Amount in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account. However, if the Depositors
fail to deposit the amount of the increase in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account on or before the Payment Date of that Subordination
Step-up Period, the Subordination Factor will automatically increase according to the definition of Subordination Factor.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Release
of Funds in Reserve Account</U>. On the earlier to occur of (i)&nbsp;the payment in full of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, and (ii)&nbsp;the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date, any funds remaining in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account will be treated as Available
Investor Principal Collections. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account will, following that occurrence, be considered to have terminated
under this Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.10.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;[Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Account].</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Initial
Accumulation Period Reserve Account Deposit</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account will be funded by the Issuer,
starting on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Funding Date, in the amount equal to the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Reserve Account Required Amount for that date and will be increased and decreased as stated in this Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Accumulation
Period Reserve Account Draw Amounts</U>. On or before each Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period, the Servicer will calculate
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Draw Amount and direct the Indenture Trustee to withdraw the amount from the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Account on that Payment Date and deposit the amount in the Collection Account for application as Available
Investor Interest Collections.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Release
of Funds in Accumulation Period Reserve Account</U>. On the earliest to occur of (i)&nbsp;the payment in full of the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes, (ii)&nbsp;the first Payment Date relating to an Early Amortization Period, and (iii)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity
Date, any funds remaining in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account will be treated as Available Investor Interest
Collections. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account will, following that occurrence, be considered to have terminated
for purposes of this Indenture Supplement.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;4.11.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Calculation
Agent; Benchmark Determination.]</U></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Appointment</U>.
The Issuer agrees that for so long as the Floating Rate Notes are Outstanding and the Benchmark is SOFR there will be an agent appointed
to determine or obtain SOFR for each Interest Period (the &quot;Calculation Agent&quot;). The Issuer appoints The Bank of New York Mellon as Calculation
Agent only for the purposes of determining or obtaining SOFR for each Interest Period and The Bank of New York Mellon accepts the appointment. The Calculation
Agent may be removed by the Issuer at any time. If the Calculation Agent is unable or unwilling to act as Calculation Agent or is removed
by the Issuer, the Issuer will promptly appoint as a replacement Calculation Agent a leading bank with the ability to determine or obtain
SOFR that is not an Affiliate of the Issuer or its Affiliates. The Calculation Agent may not resign without a replacement having been
duly appointed.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Benchmark
Determination</U>. If the Benchmark is SOFR , on each SOFR Determination Date, the Calculation Agent will notify the Servicer, the Issuer
and the Administrator by email of SOFR for the related Interest Period. If the Benchmark is any rate other than SOFR, on each Benchmark
Determination Date, the Issuer will notify the Servicer and the Indenture Trustee by email of the Benchmark for the related Interest
Period. All determinations of the Benchmark by the Calculation Agent or the Issuer, as applicable, in the absence of manifest error,
will be conclusive and binding on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Effect
of Benchmark Transition Event.</U></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Benchmark
Replacement</U>. If the Issuer determines that a Benchmark Transition Event and its related Benchmark Replacement Date have occurred
prior to the Reference Time in respect of any determination of the Benchmark on any date, the</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 20; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->17<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Benchmark
Replacement will replace the then-current Benchmark for all purposes relating to the Notes in respect of such determination on such date
and all determinations on all subsequent dates.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Benchmark
Replacement Conforming Changes</U>. In connection with the implementation of a Benchmark Replacement, the Issuer will have the right
to make Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes from time to time.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Notice
of Benchmark Replacement and/or Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes</U>. Promptly following the determination of a Benchmark Replacement
and/or the making of any Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes, the Issuer will notify the Indenture Trustee and the Servicer, and
will provide to the Servicer the relevant information regarding the Unadjusted Benchmark Replacement, the Benchmark Replacement Adjustment
and any such Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes for inclusion in the Monthly Investor Report. Notwithstanding anything in this
Indenture Supplement or the other Transaction Documents to the contrary, upon the delivery of such notice and the inclusion of such information
in the Monthly Investor Report, this Indenture Supplement and/or any other relevant Transaction Document will be deemed to have been
amended to reflect such Unadjusted Benchmark Replacement, Benchmark Replacement Adjustment and/or Benchmark Replacement Conforming Changes
without further compliance with the provisions of Article&nbsp;IX of the Indenture or the amendment provisions of any other relevant
Transaction Document.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Decisions
and Determinations</U>. Any determination, decision or election that may be made by the Issuer pursuant to this Section&nbsp;4.10(c)&nbsp;(or
pursuant to any capitalized term used in this Section&nbsp;4.10(c)&nbsp;or in any such capitalized term), including any determination
with respect to a tenor, rate or adjustment or of the occurrence or non-occurrence of an event, circumstance or date and any decision
to take or refrain from taking any action or any selection, will be conclusive and binding absent manifest error, may be made in the
Issuer's sole discretion, and, notwithstanding anything to the contrary in the Transaction Documents, will become effective without consent
from any other party. None of the Issuer, the Owner Trustee, the Indenture Trustee, the Calculation Agent, the Administrator, the Sponsor,
the Depositors or the Servicer will have any liability for any determination made by or on behalf of the Issuer pursuant to this Section&nbsp;4.10(c)&nbsp;(or
pursuant to any capitalized term used in this Section&nbsp;4.10(c)&nbsp;or in any such capitalized term), and each Noteholder and Note
Owner, by its acceptance of a Note or a beneficial interest in a Note, will be deemed to waive and release any and all claims against
the Issuer, the Owner Trustee, the Indenture Trustee, the Calculation Agent, the Administrator, the Sponsor, the Depositors and the Servicer
relating to any such determinations.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;V<BR>
THE NOTES</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Additional
Terms Applicable to the Notes</U>. The Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes and the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders and Note Owners will be subject
to the terms applicable to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes in Article&nbsp;II of the Indenture and in this Article&nbsp;V.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->18<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.2.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Note Owner Representations</U>. Each Series&nbsp;20__-__ Note Owner, by its acceptance of an interest
or participation in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, is deemed to represent, warrant and covenant to the Issuer, the Depositors and
the Indenture Trustee as follows:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>ERISA
Representations</U>. Each Class&nbsp;__ [and Class&nbsp;__] Note Owner that is (i)&nbsp;an &quot;employee benefit plan&quot; that is
subject to Title I of ERISA, (ii)&nbsp;a &quot;plan&quot; that is subject to Section&nbsp;4975 of the Code, (iii)&nbsp;an entity that
is deemed to be holding plan assets of any of the foregoing by reason of such holder's investment in the entity within the meaning of
29 C.F.R. Section&nbsp;2510.3-101, as modified by Section&nbsp;3(42) of ERISA or (iv)&nbsp;a plan that is subject to any Similar Law,
by accepting a beneficial interest in a Class&nbsp;__ [and Class&nbsp;__] Note, is deemed to represent that its purchase, holding and
disposition of that beneficial interest is not and will not result in a non-exempt prohibited transaction under Title I of ERISA or Section&nbsp;4975
of the Code or a violation of any Similar Law, as applicable.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Tax
Treatment</U>. It will treat the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes for U.S. federal, State and local income and franchise tax purposes as indebtedness
secured by the Trust Property.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.3.&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Rule&nbsp;144A Notes]</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Rule&nbsp;144A
Notes Not Registered</U>. The Class&nbsp;__ [and Class&nbsp;__] Notes ([collectively,] the &quot;<U>Rule&nbsp;144A Notes</U>&quot;) have
not been registered under the Securities Act or any State securities laws. None of the Issuer, the Depositors or the Indenture Trustee
is obligated to register the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes under the Securities Act or any State securities or &quot;blue sky&quot; laws or to
take other action not required under this Indenture Supplement, the Indenture or the Trust Agreement to permit the transfer of a Rule&nbsp;144A
Note without registration. The Issuer, at the direction of the Depositors or the Administrator, may elect to register, or cause the registration
of, the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes under the Securities Act and any applicable State securities laws. In this case, the Issuer will deliver,
or cause to be delivered, to the Indenture Trustee and the Note Registrar the Opinions of Counsel, Officer's Certificates and other information
necessary to effect the registration.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Restrictions
on Transfer</U>. Until the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes have been registered under the Securities Act and any applicable State securities laws
under Section&nbsp;5.3(a), no Rule&nbsp;144A Note may be sold, transferred, assigned, participated, pledged or disposed of (each, a &quot;<U>Rule&nbsp;144A
Note Transfer</U>&quot;) except according to this Section&nbsp;5.3, and an attempted Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer in violation of this
Section&nbsp;5.3 will be null and void (each, a &quot;<U>Void Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer</U>&quot;). Notwithstanding any other provision
of this Indenture Supplement, no Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer may be made by a Depositor or its Affiliates unless such Depositor delivers
an Opinion of Counsel to the Indenture Trustee and the Issuer stating that the transfer will not (A)&nbsp;cause any other Rule&nbsp;144A
Note to be deemed sold or exchanged for purposes of Section&nbsp;1001 of the Code, (B)&nbsp;cause the Issuer to be treated as an association
or publicly traded partnership taxable as a corporation for U.S. federal income tax purposes or (C)&nbsp;adversely affect the treatment
of any other Rule&nbsp;144A Notes as debt for U.S. federal income tax purposes.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Note
Legend and Transferee Representation</U>. Each Rule&nbsp;144A Note will bear the legend in Exhibit&nbsp;A. As a condition to the registration
of a Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer, the</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 22; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->19<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">prospective
transferee of the Rule&nbsp;144A Note will be deemed to represent to the Indenture Trustee, the Note Registrar and the Issuer the following:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;It
understands that the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes have not been registered under the Securities Act or any State securities or &quot;blue sky&quot;
laws.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;It
understands that Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfers are only permitted if made in compliance with the Securities Act and other applicable
laws and only to a person who the holder reasonably believes is a &quot;qualified institutional buyer&quot; within the meaning of Rule&nbsp;144A
(a &quot;<U>QIB</U>&quot;).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;It
(A)&nbsp;is a QIB, (B)&nbsp;is aware that the sale to it is being made under Rule&nbsp;144A and if it is acquiring the Rule&nbsp;144A
Notes or an interest or participation in the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes for the account of another QIB, that other QIB is aware that the sale
is being made under Rule&nbsp;144A and (C)&nbsp;is acquiring the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes or an interest or participation in the Rule&nbsp;144A
Notes for its own account or for the account of another QIB.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;It
is purchasing the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes for its own account or for one or more investor accounts for which it is acting as fiduciary or
agent, in each case for investment, and not with a view to offer, transfer, assign, participate, pledge or dispose of the Rule&nbsp;144A
Notes for a distribution that would violate the Securities Act.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Rule&nbsp;144A
Noteholder Agreement</U>. By acceptance of a Rule&nbsp;144A Note, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder of a Rule&nbsp;144A Note agrees
with and represents to the Depositors, the Issuer and the Note Registrar that no Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer will be made unless (i)&nbsp;the
registration requirements of the Securities Act and applicable State securities laws have been complied with for the Rule&nbsp;144A Note
according to Section&nbsp;5.3(a), (ii)&nbsp;the Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer is to a Depositor or its Affiliates or (iii)&nbsp;the Rule&nbsp;144A
Note Transfer is exempt from the registration requirements under the Securities Act because the Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer is in compliance
with Rule&nbsp;144A, to a transferee who the transferor reasonably believes is a QIB that is purchasing for its own account or for the
account of a QIB and to whom notice is given that the Rule&nbsp;144A Note Transfer is being made under Rule&nbsp;144A.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Rule&nbsp;144A
Information</U>. The Depositors will make available to the prospective transferor and transferee of a Rule&nbsp;144A Note information
requested to satisfy the requirements of paragraph (d)(4)&nbsp;of Rule&nbsp;144A (the &quot;<U>Rule&nbsp;144A Information</U>&quot;).
The Rule&nbsp;144A Information will include any of the following items requested by the prospective transferee:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
offering memorandum, if any, relating to the Rule&nbsp;144A Notes and any amendments or supplements to the offering memorandum;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
Monthly Investor Report for each Payment Date before the request;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;copies
of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Documents, including any amendments; and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 23; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->20<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
