    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;any
other information reasonably available to the Depositors that may be considered Rule&nbsp;144A Information.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.4.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Communications by Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Noteholder
Communications with Indenture Trustee</U>. A Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder (if the Notes are represented by Definitive Notes) or a Note
Owner (if the Notes are represented by Book-Entry Notes) may communicate with the Indenture Trustee and give notices and make requests
and demands and give directions to the Indenture Trustee through the procedures of the Clearing Agency and by notifying the Indenture
Trustee. Any Note Owner must provide a written certification stating that the Note Owner is a beneficial owner of a Series&nbsp;20__-__
Note, together with supporting documentation such as a trade confirmation, an account statement, a letter from a broker or dealer verifying
ownership or another similar document evidencing ownership of a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Note. The Indenture Trustee will not be required
to take action in response to requests, demands or directions of a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or a Note Owner, other than requests,
demands or directions relating to an asset representations review demand under Section&nbsp;5.5, unless the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder
or Note Owner has offered reasonable security or indemnity reasonably satisfactory to the Indenture Trustee to protect it against the
fees and expenses that it may incur in complying with the request, demand or direction.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Communications
between Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders</U>. A Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder (if the Notes are represented by Definitive Notes) or a
Note Owner (if the Notes are represented by Book-Entry Notes) that seeks to communicate with other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or
Note Owners, as applicable, about a possible exercise of rights under this Indenture Supplement or the other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction
Documents may send a request to the Issuer or the Servicer, on behalf of the Issuer, to include information regarding the communication
in a Form&nbsp;10-D to be filed by the Issuer with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Each request must include (i)&nbsp;the name
of the requesting Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner, (ii)&nbsp;the method by which other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or
Note Owners, as applicable, may contact the requesting Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner and (iii)&nbsp;in the case of a Note
Owner, a certification from that Person that it is a Note Owner, together with at least one form of documentation evidencing its ownership
of a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Note, including a trade confirmation, account statement, letter from a broker or dealer or similar document.
A Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner, as applicable, that delivers a request under this Section&nbsp;5.4(b)&nbsp;will be deemed
to have certified to the Issuer and the Servicer that its request to communicate with other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners,
as applicable, relates solely to a possible exercise of rights under this Indenture or the other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Documents,
and will not be used for other purposes. The Issuer will promptly deliver any request to the Servicer. On receipt of a request, the Servicer
will include in the Form&nbsp;10-D filed by the Issuer with the Securities and Exchange Commission for the Collection Period in which
the request was received (A)&nbsp;a statement that the Issuer has received a request from a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner,
as applicable, that is interested in communicating with other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners, as applicable, about a
possible exercise of rights under this Indenture or the other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Transaction Documents, (B)&nbsp;the name of the requesting
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner, (C)&nbsp;the date the request was received and (D)&nbsp;a description of the method by
which the other Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 24; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->21<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Note
Owners, as applicable, may contact the requesting Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder or Note Owner.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.5.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder Demand for Asset Representations Review</U>. If a Status
Trigger occurs, as reported on Form&nbsp;10-D, a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholder (if the Notes are represented by Definitive Notes)
or a Note Owner (if the Notes are represented by Book-Entry Notes) may make a demand on the Indenture Trustee to cause a vote of the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners, as applicable, about whether to direct the Asset Representations Reviewer to conduct
a Review of the Review Receivables under the Asset Representations Review Agreement. In the case of a Note Owner, each demand must
be accompanied by a certification from that Person that it is a Note Owner, together with at least one form of documentation
evidencing its ownership of a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Note, including a trade confirmation, account statement, letter from a broker or
dealer or similar document. If the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners, of at least 5% of the aggregate Note Balance of
the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes demand a vote within 90 days of the filing of the Form&nbsp;10-D reporting the occurrence of the
Status Trigger, the Indenture Trustee will promptly request a vote of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners of record
as of the most recent Record Date and, in the case of Note Owners, through the Clearing Agency process. The vote will remain open
until the 150th day after the filing of the Form&nbsp;10-D. Assuming a voting quorum of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note
Owners holding at least 5% of the aggregate Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes is reached, if the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Noteholders or Note Owners of a majority of the Note Balance of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes voted to direct a Review, the Indenture
Trustee will promptly send a Review Notice to the Asset Representations Reviewer and the Servicer under the Asset Representations
Review Agreement stating that the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders or Note Owners have voted to direct the Asset Representations
Reviewer to conduct the Review.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;5.6.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;<U>Tax Information</U>. If (a)&nbsp;a member of any &quot;expanded group&quot; (as defined in Treasury Regulation
Section&nbsp;1.385-1(c)(4)) that includes the Issuer, or (b)&nbsp;a &quot;controlled partnership&quot; (as defined in Treasury
Regulation Section&nbsp;1.385-1(c)(1)) of an &quot;expanded group&quot; described in clause (i), acquires any Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes, and those Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes are recharacterized as stock pursuant to Section&nbsp;385 of the Code, and the holder of
those Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes recharacterized as stock subsequently transfers the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes to a Person that is
not described in either clause (a)&nbsp;or (b), then on request by that Person, the Issuer will provide or cause to be provided
information reasonably requested by that Person to determine the issue date and issue price of the transferred Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;VI<BR>
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Events</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;6.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Events</U>. Any of the following events for the
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be an Amortization Event:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Failure
to Make Required Payments; Failure to Perform</U>. Either Depositor fails (i)&nbsp;to make any payment or deposit required to be made
under the related Sale and Servicing Agreement, the Indenture or this Indenture Supplement on or before the date occurring five Business
Days after the date the payment or deposit is required to be made or (ii)&nbsp;to observe or perform in any material respect any other
covenants or agreements of that Depositor in the</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 25; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->22<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">related
Sale and Servicing Agreement, the Indenture or this Indenture Supplement that has an Adverse Effect and continues for 60 days after the
Depositor receives notice from the Indenture Trustee of the failure, requiring it to be corrected, and the failure continues to have
an Adverse Effect for that 60-day period;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Representations
and Warranties</U>. Any representation or warranty made by either Depositor in the related Sale and Servicing Agreement, the Indenture
or this Indenture Supplement, or any information contained in a computer file or other list required to be delivered by that Depositor
under the related Sale and Servicing Agreement, proves to have been incorrect in any material respect when made or when delivered and
has an Adverse Effect, which continues to be incorrect in any material respect for 60 days after the Depositor receives notice from the
Indenture Trustee of the failure, requiring it to be corrected, and the failure continues to have an Adverse Effect for that 60-day period.
However, a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Event under this subsection (b)&nbsp;will be considered corrected if that Depositor has accepted
reassignment of the related Receivable, or all those Receivables, if applicable, during that period according to the related Sale and
Servicing Agreement;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Servicer
Termination Event</U>. A Servicer Termination Event occurs that has an Adverse Effect;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Expected
Final Payment Date</U>. The Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes is not paid in full on the Expected Final Payment Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Monthly
Principal Payment Rate</U>. The average of the Monthly Principal Payment Rates for the three prior Collection Periods is less than __%;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Required
Subordinated Amount</U>. On any Determination Date, the Available Subordinated Amount for the next Payment Date will be less than the
Required Subordinated Amount after giving effect to any payments to be made on that Payment Date, and continues unremedied for five Business
Days after that Payment Date. For the purpose of determining whether a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Event has occurred under this
subsection (f), any reduction of the Available Subordinated Amount resulting from reallocations of the Available Depositor Principal
Collections to pay interest on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes if the Benchmark is equal to or greater than the prime rate on which interest
on the receivables is calculated on the applicable Benchmark Determination Date will be considered a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization
Event only if Benchmark remains equal to or greater than the prime rate for the next 30 consecutive days following that Benchmark Determination
Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(g)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Excess
Funding Account</U>. The amounts in the Excess Funding Account exceed __% of the sum of the &quot;Adjusted Invested Amounts&quot; of
all Series&nbsp;for three consecutive Collection Periods, after giving effect to any payments to be made on each related Payment Date;
or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(h)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Acceleration
of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes</U>. An Event of Default for Series&nbsp;20__-__ occurs and the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes are accelerated
under Section&nbsp;5.2 of the Indenture.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">If
an event described in subsections (a)&nbsp;through (c)&nbsp;above occurs and is continuing, either the Indenture Trustee or the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Noteholders of a majority of the Note Balance of the</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 26; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->23<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes by notifying the Depositors and the Servicer (and to the Indenture Trustee if given by the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders) may
declare that an Amortization Event for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes (a &quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Event</U>&quot;) has
occurred. If an event described in subsections (d)&nbsp;through (h)&nbsp;above occurs, a Series&nbsp;20__-__ Amortization Event will
occur immediately without any notice or other action by the Indenture Trustee or the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;VII<BR>
[redemption of notes]; series final maturity</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;7.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;<U>[Redemption</U>.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>[Optional
Redemption</U>. The Issuer has the option to permit the Depositors to increase the Depositor Interest by causing the Issuer to redeem
the Notes in whole, but not in part, (i)&nbsp;on any Payment Date during the Note Redemption Period, including the Expected Final Payment
Date, without any Make-Whole Payment and (ii)&nbsp;on any earlier Payment Date with a Make-Whole Payment. If the Notes are to be redeemed
under this Section&nbsp;7.1, the Servicer or the Issuer will notify the Indenture Trustee and the Rating Agencies at least ten days before
the Redemption Date. After the Servicer or the Issuer notifies the Indenture Trustee, the Indenture Trustee will promptly notify the
Noteholders:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;of
the Redemption Date;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(ii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;of
the Note Redemption Price;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iii)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;of
the outstanding Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;of the Notes to be redeemed and that the Notes plus accrued and unpaid interest, Make-Whole
Payments and Step-Up Amounts on the Notes to the Redemption Date will be paid in full;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(iv)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;of
the place to surrender the Notes for final payment (which will be the office or agency of the Issuer maintained under Section&nbsp;3.2
of the Indenture); and</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0.5in; text-indent: 0.75in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(v)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;that
on the Redemption Date, the outstanding Note Balance of the Notes plus accrued and unpaid interest on the Notes will become due and payable
and that interest on the Notes will cease to accrue from and after the Redemption Date, unless the Issuer fails to pay the Notes on the
Redemption Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Deposit
of Note Redemption Price</U>. If the Notes are to be redeemed under this Section&nbsp;7.1, the Issuer will cause the Depositors to deposit
on the Business Day before the Redemption Date (or, with satisfaction of the Rating Agency Condition, on the Redemption Date) in the
Collection Account the sum of (A)&nbsp;the Note Redemption Price for the Notes and (B)&nbsp;all other amounts payable by the Issuer under
this Indenture Supplement on such payment Date, and the Notes will be paid in full on the Redemption Date. For the avoidance of doubt,
the Depositors may satisfy their obligation to pay the Note Redemption Price, in whole or in part, by causing the Issuer to issue one
or more Series&nbsp;of Notes, re-open an existing Series&nbsp;of Notes or draw on an existing Variable Funding Note Series, on or before
the Redemption Date and causing the proceeds of such issuance, re-opening or drawing to be deposited in the Collection Account.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 27; Value: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">&nbsp;<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->24<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Release
of Funds</U>. On the Redemption Date, the outstanding Note Balance of the Notes plus accrued and unpaid interest on the Notes will become
due and payable and that interest on the Notes will cease to accrue from and after the Redemption Date, unless the Issuer fails to pay
the Notes on the Redemption Date. On redemption, the Indenture Trustee will release to the Issuer or any other Person entitled to funds
then in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts under this Indenture Supplement according to Section&nbsp;4.7(f).]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;7.2.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;<U>Series&nbsp;Final Maturity.</U></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Reassignment
Amount; Liquidation Proceeds</U>. If the Sold Receivables are reassigned under Section&nbsp;2.3(c)&nbsp;or 6.1(b)&nbsp;of the Sale and
Servicing Agreements, the Reassignment Amount will be paid to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders on the first Payment Date after the
Collection Period in which the reassignment occurs. If the Collateral allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__ is liquidated under Section&nbsp;5.6(c)&nbsp;of
the Indenture, the proceeds from the liquidation will be paid to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders on the first Payment Date after
the Collection Period in which the liquidation occurs. If the Indenture Trustee has received the Monthly Investor Report by the related
Determination Date, the Indenture Trustee will (based on the information in the Monthly Investor Report) make payments or distributions
of the Reassignment Amount or the proceeds from any liquidation of Collateral allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__ under Section&nbsp;5.6(c)&nbsp;of
the Indenture according to Section&nbsp;4.2 on the related Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Payment
in Full</U>. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Indenture Supplement, the Indenture or the Sale and Servicing Agreements,
(i)&nbsp;all amounts distributed to the Note Paying Agent under Section&nbsp;7.2(a)&nbsp;for payment to the Series&nbsp;20__-__Noteholders
will be considered paid in full to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders on the date the funds are distributed to the Note Paying Agent
under this Section&nbsp;7.2(b)&nbsp;and will be considered to be a final payment of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes and (ii)&nbsp;if the
amounts available for final payment to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders and to the Noteholders of any other Series&nbsp;on any Payment
Date are less than the amount required to be so paid, the available amounts will be allocated to each Series&nbsp;based on the respective
amounts required to be paid to each Series&nbsp;on that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase">ARTICLE&nbsp;VIII<BR>
Miscellaneous Provisions</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;8.1.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Ratification of Agreement</U>. The Indenture, as supplemented by this Indenture Supplement, will continue in
full force and effect and is ratified and confirmed.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;8.2.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<B><U>GOVERNING LAW</U>. THIS INDENTURE SUPPLEMENT AND EACH SERIES 20__-__ NOTE WILL BE GOVERNED BY AND
CONSTRUED ACCORDING TO THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK.</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Section&nbsp;8.3.&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;
 &#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;<U>Counterparts</U>. This Indenture Supplement may be executed in multiple counterparts. Each
counterpart will be an original and all counterparts will together be one document.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[Remainder
of Page&nbsp;Left Blank]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Appendix
A<BR>
to Indenture Supplement</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Usage
and Definitions</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Ford
Credit Floorplan Master Owner Trust A<BR>
Series&nbsp;20__-__</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"><U>Usage</U></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">The
following usage rules&nbsp;apply to this Appendix, any document that incorporates this Appendix and any document delivered under any
such document:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;The
term &quot;document&quot; includes any document, agreement, instrument, certificate, notice, report, statement or other writing, whether
in electronic or physical form.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;Accounting
terms not defined or not completely defined in this Appendix will have the meanings given to them under generally accepted accounting
principles, international financial reporting standards or other applicable accounting principles in effect in the United States on the
date of the document that incorporates this Appendix.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;References
to &quot;Article,&quot; &quot;Section,&quot; &quot;Exhibit,&quot; &quot;Schedule,&quot; &quot;Appendix&quot; or another subdivision of
or to an attachment are, unless otherwise stated, to an article, section, exhibit, schedule, appendix or subdivision of or an attachment
to the document in which the reference appears.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;Any
document defined or referred to in this Appendix or in any document that incorporates this Appendix means the document as amended, modified,
supplemented, restated or replaced, including by waiver or consent, and includes all attachments to and instruments incorporated in the
document.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(e)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;Any
statute defined or referred to in this Appendix or in any document that incorporates this Appendix means the statute as amended, modified,
supplemented, restated or replaced, including by succession of comparable successor statute, and includes any rules&nbsp;and regulations
under the statute and any judicial and administrative interpretations of the statute.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(f)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;References
to &quot;law&quot; or &quot;applicable law&quot; in this Appendix or in any document that incorporates this Appendix include all rules&nbsp;and
regulations enacted under such law.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(g)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;The
calculation of any amount as of the Series&nbsp;Cutoff Date will be determined as of the open of business on that day before the application
or processing of any funds, payments and other transactions on that day. The calculation of any amount for any other day will be determined,
unless otherwise stated, as of the close of business on that day after the application or processing of any funds, payments and other
transactions on that day.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(h)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;References
to deposits, transfers and payments of any funds refer to deposits, transfers or payments of such funds in immediately available funds.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 30; Options: NewSection; Value: 1 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->1<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(i)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;The
terms defined in this Appendix apply to the singular and plural forms of those terms and may be used as nouns or verbs. Terms defined
in the present tense may be used in the past or future tense.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(j)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;The
term &quot;including&quot; means &quot;including without limitation.&quot;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(k)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;References
to a Person are also to its permitted successors and assigns, whether in its individual or representative capacity.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(l)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;In
the computation of periods of time from one date to or through a later date, the word &quot;from&quot; means &quot;from and including,&quot;
the word &quot;to&quot; means &quot;to but excluding,&quot; and the word &quot;through&quot; means &quot;to and including.&quot;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(m)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;Except
where &quot;not less than zero&quot; or similar language is indicated, amounts determined by reference to a mathematical formula may
be positive or negative.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(n)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;References
to a month, quarter or year are, unless otherwise stated, to a calendar month, calendar quarter or calendar year.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(o)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;No
Person will be deemed to have &quot;knowledge&quot; of a particular event or occurrence for purposes of any document that incorporates
this Appendix, unless either (i)&nbsp;a Responsible Person of the Person has actual knowledge of the event or occurrence or (ii)&nbsp;the
Person has received notice of the event or occurrence according to any Transaction Document.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"><U>Definitions</U></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Accrued
Note Interest</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date, the sum of the Note Monthly Interest and the Note Interest Shortfall
for that Class.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Accumulation
Period Factor</U>&quot; means, for any Collection Period, a fraction with:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            numerator equal to the sum of the &quot;Initial Invested Amounts&quot; of all Series&nbsp;in
                                            Principal Sharing Group One; and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            denominator equal to the sum of (i)&nbsp;the Initial Invested Amount, plus (ii)&nbsp;the
                                            &quot;Initial Invested Amounts&quot; of all Series&nbsp;in Principal Sharing Group One, other
                                            than Series&nbsp;20__-__, that are not expected to be in their &quot;Revolving Periods&quot;
                                            from that date to the Expected Final Payment Date.]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Accumulation
Period Length</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the number of Collection Periods needed for the sum of the Accumulation Period
Factors for those Collection Periods to be equal to or greater than the Required Accumulation Factor Number for that Determination Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Accrued
Step-Up Amounts</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date after the Expected Final Payment Date, the sum of the Step-Up Amounts
and the Step-Up Shortfall.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->2<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Adjusted
Invested Amount</U>&quot; means, as of a date, (a)&nbsp;the Invested Amount, minus (b)&nbsp;during [an Accumulation Period,] the Required
Amortization Period or an Early Amortization Period for Series&nbsp;20__-__, the amount of any Principal Collections in the Collection
Account allocable to Series&nbsp;20__-__, <U>minus</U> (c)&nbsp;the amount in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account (excluding
any net investment earnings), each as of that date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Asset
Representations Review Agreement</U>&quot; means the Asset Representations Review Agreement, dated as of _________, 20__, among the Issuer,
the Servicer and the Asset Representations Reviewer.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Asset
Representations Reviewer</U>&quot; means Clayton Fixed Income Services LLC, a Delaware limited liability company.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Available
Investor Interest Collections</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to the sum of (a)&nbsp;the Investor Interest Collections
for the related Collection Period, plus (b)&nbsp;any net investment earnings on amounts in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accounts for the related
Collection Period, plus (c)&nbsp;[the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Draw Amount] the Monthly Depositor Servicing Fee
for that Payment Date, plus (d)&nbsp;[on the termination of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account under Section&nbsp;4.7(a)(iii)&nbsp;of
the Indenture Supplement, all remaining amounts in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account (excluding any net investment
earnings,)] any Available Investor Principal Collections treated as Available Investor Interest Collections pursuant to Section&nbsp;4.2(c)(iv)&nbsp;of
the Indenture Supplement, plus (e)&nbsp;if the Payment Date is the Redemption Date, the portion of the Note Redemption Price in excess
of the Note Balance as of such Redemption Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Available
Investor Principal Collections</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to the excess of (a)&nbsp;the sum of (i)&nbsp;the
Investor Principal Collections for the related Collection Period, <U>plus</U> (ii)&nbsp;any Available Investor Interest Collections,
Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Available Amounts, Excess Interest Collections from other Series&nbsp;in Excess Interest Sharing
Group One and Available Depositor Collections that, under Sections 4.2(a)&nbsp;and (b)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement, are to be treated
as Available Investor Principal Collections for that Payment Date, <U>plus</U> (iii)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Excess Funding Amount,
<U>plus</U> (iv)&nbsp;any Shared Principal Collections for other Series&nbsp;in Principal Sharing Group One (including any amounts in
the Excess Funding Account that are made available to Series&nbsp;20__-__ under the Indenture as Shared Principal Collections), <U>plus
</U>(v)&nbsp;on the termination of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account under Section&nbsp;4.9(c)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement,
all remaining amounts in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account (excluding any net investment earnings and after giving effect to Section&nbsp;4.2(b)(iii))
of the Indenture Supplement, plus (vi)&nbsp;if the Payment Date is the Redemption Date, the portion of the Note Redemption Price equal
to the Note Balance as of such Redemption Date, over (b)&nbsp;any Reallocated Principal Collections for that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Available
Subordinated Amount</U>&quot; means (a)&nbsp;for the first Determination Date after the Closing Date, an amount equal to the Required
Subordinated Amount for the first Determination Date and (b)&nbsp;for any later Determination Date, an amount equal to the lesser of
(i)&nbsp;the Required Subordinated Amount for that Determination Date and (ii)&nbsp;an amount equal to:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">

Replacement Date:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

sum of (i)&nbsp;the alternate rate of interest that has been selected or recommended by the Relevant Governmental Body as the replacement
for the then-current Benchmark for the applicable Corresponding Tenor and (ii)&nbsp;the Benchmark Replacement Adjustment; or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the

the then-current Benchmark for the applicable Corresponding Tenor and (ii)&nbsp;the Benchmark Replacement Adjustment.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Benchmark
Replacement Adjustment</U>&quot; means the first alternative set forth in the order below that can be determined by the Issuer as of
the Benchmark Replacement Date:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
spread adjustment (which may be a positive or negative value or zero), or method for calculating or determining such spread adjustment,
that has been selected or recommended by the Relevant Governmental Body for the applicable Unadjusted Benchmark Replacement; or</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the

that has been selected by the Issuer in its reasonable discretion for the replacement of the then-current Benchmark with the applicable
Unadjusted Benchmark Replacement.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Benchmark
Replacement Conforming Changes</U>&quot; means, with respect to any Benchmark Replacement, any technical, administrative or operational
changes (including changes to the definitions of &quot;Benchmark Determination Date,&quot; &quot;Interest Period,&quot; and &quot;Reference
Time,&quot; the timing and frequency of determining rates, the process of making payments of interest, rounding of amounts or tenors
and other administrative matters) that the Issuer decides may be appropriate to reflect the adoption of such Benchmark Replacement in
a manner substantially consistent with market practice (or, if the Issuer decides that adoption of any portion of such market practice
is not administratively feasible or if the Issuer determines that no market practice for use of the Benchmark Replacement exists, in
such other manner as the Issuer determines is reasonably necessary).]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Benchmark
Replacement Date</U>&quot; means:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">in
                                            the case of clause (a)&nbsp;or (b)&nbsp;of the definition of &quot;Benchmark Transition Event,&quot;
                                            the later of (i)&nbsp;the date of the public statement or publication of information referenced
                                            therein and (ii)&nbsp;the date on which the administrator of the Benchmark permanently or
                                            indefinitely ceases to provide the Benchmark; or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">in
                                            the case of clause (c)&nbsp;of the definition of &quot;Benchmark Transition Event,&quot;
                                            the date of the public statement or publication of information referenced therein.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">For
the avoidance of doubt, if the event giving rise to the Benchmark Replacement Date occurs on a Benchmark Determination Date, but earlier
than the Reference Time for that</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->5<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Benchmark
Determination Date, the Benchmark Replacement Date will be deemed to have occurred prior to the Reference Time for such determination.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Benchmark
Transition Event</U>&quot; means the occurrence of one or more of the following events with respect to the then-current Benchmark:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            public statement or publication of information by or on behalf of the administrator of the
                                            Benchmark announcing that such administrator has ceased or will cease to provide the Benchmark,
                                            permanently or indefinitely; <U>provided</U>, that, at the time of such statement or publication,
                                            there is no successor administrator that will continue to provide the Benchmark;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            public statement or publication of information by the regulatory supervisor for the administrator
                                            of the Benchmark, the central bank for the currency of the Benchmark, an insolvency official
                                            with jurisdiction over the administrator for the Benchmark, a resolution authority with jurisdiction
                                            over the administrator for the Benchmark or a court or an entity with similar insolvency
                                            or resolution authority over the administrator for the Benchmark, which states that the administrator
                                            of the Benchmark has ceased or will cease to provide the Benchmark permanently or indefinitely;
                                            <U>provided</U>, that, at the time of such statement or publication, there is no successor
                                            administrator that will continue to provide the Benchmark; or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            public statement or publication of information by the regulatory supervisor for the administrator
                                            of the Benchmark announcing that the Benchmark is no longer representative of the underlying
                                            market or economic reality or may no longer be used.]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Agent</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;4.11 of the Indenture Supplement.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

means the Class&nbsp;A[-1], [Class&nbsp;A-2,] Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D Notes, as applicable.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">cumulative
