<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Closing
Date</U>&quot; means ________, 20__.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Corresponding
Tenor</U>&quot; means, with respect to a Benchmark Replacement, a tenor (including overnight) having approximately the same length (disregarding
business day adjustment) as the applicable tenor for the then-current Benchmark.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Controlled
Accumulation Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period, an amount equal to the Initial Invested
Amount <U>divided by</U> six, except that, if the Controlled Accumulation Period starts after _______ 20__, the Controlled Accumulation
Amount for each Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period will be equal to (a)&nbsp;the product of (i)&nbsp;the Initial Invested
Amount, <U>times</U> (ii)&nbsp;the Accumulation Period Factor for the last Collection Period of the Revolving Period, <U>divided by</U>
(b)&nbsp;the Required Accumulation Factor Number for the last Determination Date during the Revolving Period.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Controlled
Accumulation Period</U>&quot; means, unless an Early Amortization Period has started before that period, the period starting on the first
day of the _______ 20__ Collection Period or a later date as is determined according to Section&nbsp;4.2(g)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement
and ending on the earlier to occur of (a)&nbsp;the day before the start of the Early Amortization Period and (b)&nbsp;the end of the
Collection Period before the Payment Date on which the Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will be paid in full.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 36; Value: 1 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->7<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Controlled
Deposit Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period, an amount equal to the sum of (a)&nbsp;the
Controlled Accumulation Amount for that Payment Date and (b)&nbsp;any Deficit Controlled Accumulation Amount for the prior Payment Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Dealer
Overconcentration</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of Receivables
originated in all Accounts of a Dealer or a group of affiliated Dealers on the last day of the related Collection Period, <U>over</U>
(b)(i)&nbsp;in the case of Dealers affiliated with AutoNation,&nbsp;Inc., __%, (ii)&nbsp;in the case of Dealers affiliated with Lithia
Motors,&nbsp;Inc., __%, and (iii)&nbsp;for all other Dealers or groups of affiliated Dealers, __%, in each case, of the Pool Balance
on the last day of that Collection Period (or, in any case, a higher percentage if the Rating Agency Condition has been satisfied).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Defaulted
Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, an amount (not less than zero) equal to (a)&nbsp;the principal amount of all Receivables
that became Defaulted Receivables during the related Collection Period, <U>minus</U> (b)&nbsp;the amount of the Defaulted Receivables
that are reassigned to the Depositors according to the Sale and Servicing Agreements (except that if an Insolvency Event of a Depositor
occurs, the amount of the Defaulted Receivables that are reassigned to that Depositor will be zero), <U>minus</U> (c)&nbsp;the amount
of the Defaulted Receivables that are assigned to the Servicer according to the Sale and Servicing Agreements (which will be zero if
an Insolvency Event of the Servicer occurs).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Deficit
Controlled Accumulation Amount</U>&quot; means (a)&nbsp;for the first Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period, the excess,
if any, of the Controlled Accumulation Amount for that Payment Date, <U>over</U> the amount deposited in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal
Funding Account on that Payment Date and (b)&nbsp;for each later Payment Date for the Controlled Accumulation Period, the excess, if
any, of the Controlled Deposit Amount for that Payment Date, <U>over</U> the amount deposited in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding
Account on that Payment Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Development
Dealer Overconcentration</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of
Receivables that are Development Dealer Receivables on the last day of the related Collection Period, <U>over</U> (b)&nbsp;__% of the
Pool Balance on the last day of that Collection Period (or, a higher percentage if the Rating Agency Condition has been satisfied).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Distribution
Compliance Period</U>&quot; means the period from the Closing Date to the 40th day after the Closing Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Early
Amortization Period</U>&quot; means the period starting on the day on which an Amortization Event for Series&nbsp;20__-__ occurs (or,
if the Servicer is not required to make daily deposits of Collections in the Collection Account under Section&nbsp;8.4(b)&nbsp;of the
Indenture, starting on the first day of the Collection Period in which the Amortization Event occurs) and ending on the earlier to occur
of (a)&nbsp;the end of the Collection Period before the Payment Date on which the Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes will
be paid in full and (b)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Final Maturity Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>ERISA</U>&quot;
means the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 37; Value: 1 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->8<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Excess
Funding Period</U>&quot; means the period (i)&nbsp;beginning on any Payment Date for which the amount in the Excess Funding Account exceeds
[30]% of the sum of the &quot;Adjusted Invested Amounts&quot; of all Series&nbsp;for the related Collection Period, after giving effect
to any payments to be made on each related Payment Date and (ii)&nbsp;ending on any Payment Date for which the amount in the Excess Funding
Account is equal to or less than [30]% of the sum of the &quot;Adjusted Invested Amounts&quot; of all Series, after giving effect to
any payments to be made on each related Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Excess
Interest Collections</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the Available Investor Interest
Collections for that Payment Date, <U>over</U> (b)&nbsp;the amount required to be paid, without duplication, under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through
(xv)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement on that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Expected
Final Payment Date</U>&quot; means the _________ 20__ Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Federal
Reserve Bank of New York's Website</U>&quot; means the website of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, currently at <I>https://apps.newyorkfed.org/markets/autorates/sofr-avg-ind</I>,
or at such other page&nbsp;as may replace such page&nbsp;on the website of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Fixed
Investor Percentage</U>&quot; means, for a Deposit Date or Collection Period (or portion of a Collection Period occurring after the end
of the Revolving Period), the percentage equivalent (not to exceed 100%) of a fraction with (a)&nbsp;a numerator equal to the Invested
Amount on the last day of the Revolving Period and (b)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the greater of (i)&nbsp;the Adjusted Pool Balance
on the last day of the prior Collection Period and (ii)&nbsp;the sum of the numerators used to calculate the applicable &quot;Investor
Percentages&quot; for allocating Principal Collections to all Series&nbsp;for that Collection Period, except that, for any Deposit Date
or Collection Period occurring after the Collection Period on the last day of which the Adjusted Invested Amount is zero, the Fixed Investor
Percentage will be zero.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Fleet
Overconcentration</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of the Receivables
that are Fleet Receivables on the last day of the related Collection Period, <U>over</U> (b)&nbsp;__% of the Pool Balance on the last
day of that Collection Period (or a higher percentage if the Rating Agency Condition has been satisfied).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Floating
Investor Percentage</U>&quot; means, for a Deposit Date or Collection Period (or portion of a Collection Period occurring before the
end of the Revolving Period), the percentage equivalent (not to exceed 100%) of a fraction with (a)&nbsp;a numerator equal to the Adjusted
Invested Amount on the last day of the prior Collection Period (or for the first Collection Period, the initial Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes) and (b)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the Adjusted Pool Balance on the last day of the prior Collection Period (or for the first
Collection Period, the Adjusted Pool Balance as of the Series&nbsp;Cutoff Date).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Floating
Rate Notes</U>&quot; means the Class&nbsp;A-2[, Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D] Notes.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->9<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="break-before: page; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Incremental
Subordinated Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the product of:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">a
                                            fraction with (i)&nbsp;a numerator equal to an amount (not less than zero) equal to (A)&nbsp;the
                                            Adjusted Invested Amount as of the related Payment Date, <U>plus</U> (B)&nbsp;the product
                                            of the initial Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes <U>times</U> the excess of the
                                            Required Pool Percentage over 100%, <U>plus</U> (C)&nbsp;the Required Subordinated Amount
                                            on that Determination Date (excluding the Supplemental Subordinated Percentage, if any, from
                                            the Subordinated Percentage, and without giving effect to the Incremental Subordinated Amount),
                                            <U>minus</U> (D)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Excess Funding Amount as of that Determination
                                            Date and (ii)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the Pool Balance on that Determination Date; <U>times</U></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            Non-Conforming Receivable Amount on that Determination Date.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Indenture
Supplement</U>&quot; means, for Series&nbsp;20__-__, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Indenture Supplement, dated as of ________, 20__, between
the Issuer and the Indenture Trustee.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Initial
Invested Amount</U>&quot; means, for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes and for a date, $__________. However, the Initial Invested Amount
will be reduced by the initial Note Balance of any Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes that are no longer Outstanding on the day before the start
of the Early Amortization Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Interest
Collections Shortfall</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the amount required to
be paid, without duplication, under Sections 4.2(a)(i)&nbsp;through (xv)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement on that Payment Date, <U>over
</U>(b)&nbsp;the Available Investor Interest Collections for that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Interest
Period</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date (a)&nbsp;for each Class&nbsp;of Notes, except the Floating Rate Notes, from the 15th day of
the month before the Payment Date to the 15th day of the month in which the Payment Date occurs (or from the Closing Date to __________,
20__ for the first Payment Date), and (b)&nbsp;for the Floating Rate Notes, from the prior Payment Date to the Payment Date (or from
the Closing Date to __________, 20__ for the first Payment Date).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Invested
Amount</U>&quot; means, as of a date, an amount equal to (a)&nbsp;the initial Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, <U>minus
</U>(b)&nbsp;the aggregate amount of any principal payments made to the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Noteholders before that date, <U>minus</U>
(c)&nbsp;the cumulative amount of unreimbursed Investor Charge-Offs applied to reduce the Invested Amount under Section&nbsp;4.3 of the
Indenture Supplement before that date, <U>minus</U> (d)&nbsp;the cumulative amount of unreimbursed Reallocated Principal Collections
applied to reduce the Invested Amount under Section&nbsp;4.4 of the Indenture Supplement before that date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Investor
Charge-Off</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, the excess, if any, of the amount of the unfunded Investor Default Amount for that Payment
Date <U>over</U> the amount of the Investor Default Amount applied to reduce the Available Subordinated Amount under Section&nbsp;4.3
of the Indenture Supplement for that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->10<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Investor
Default Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to the product of (a)&nbsp;the Floating Investor Percentage for the
related Collection Period, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;the Defaulted Amount for that Collection Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Investor
Interest Collections</U>&quot; means, for a Deposit Date or Collection Period, an amount equal to [the sum of (a)] the product of (i)&nbsp;the
Floating Investor Percentage for the related Collection Period, <U>times</U> (ii)&nbsp;the Interest Collections for that Deposit Date
or Collection Period, as applicable[, <U>plus</U>, (b)&nbsp;the Yield Supplement Interest Collections for that Deposit Date or Collection
Period].</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Make-Whole
Payment</U>&quot; means, for any payment of the Note Balance of a Class&nbsp;made on a Payment Date before the start of the Note Redemption
Period as a result of the occurrence of a Redemption Date, an amount (not less than zero) equal to:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">for
                                            each Class&nbsp;of Notes [other than the Floating Rate Notes,] the excess of (1)&nbsp;the
                                            present value of (i)&nbsp;the amount of all future interest payments that would otherwise
                                            accrue on the Note Balance of that Class&nbsp;at the Note Interest Rate for that Class&nbsp;on
                                            such Payment Date until the start of the Note Redemption Period and (ii)&nbsp;the principal
                                            payment, discounted from the Payment Date on which such payment would have been made to such
                                            Payment Date monthly on a 30/360 basis at the sum of (i)&nbsp;(A)&nbsp;for the Class&nbsp;A-1
                                            Notes, ___%, and (B)&nbsp;for the Class&nbsp;B, Class&nbsp;C and Class&nbsp;D Notes, ___%
                                            plus (ii)&nbsp;the higher of (A)&nbsp;zero and (B)&nbsp;the current maturity matched U.S.
                                            Treasury rate over (2)&nbsp;the principal payment, and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[for
                                            the Floating Rate Notes, the excess of (1)&nbsp;the present value of (i)&nbsp;the amount
                                            of all future interest payments that would otherwise accrue on the Note Balance of the Floating
                                            Rate Notes at the Note Interest Rate for the Floating Rate Notes on such Payment Date until
                                            the start of the Note Redemption Period and (ii)&nbsp;the principal payment, discounted from
                                            the Payment Date on which such payment would have been made to such Payment Date monthly
                                            on an actual/360 basis at the Benchmark for the Floating Rate Notes and such Payment Date
                                            over (2)&nbsp;the principal payment].]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Investor
Percentage</U>&quot; means, for a Collection Period (a)&nbsp;for Interest Collections and Defaulted Amounts at any time and Principal
Collections during the Revolving Period, the Floating Investor Percentage and (b)&nbsp;for Principal Collections during the [Controlled
Accumulation Period,] Required Amortization or the Early Amortization Period, the Fixed Investor Percentage.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Investor
Principal Collections</U>&quot; means, for a Deposit Date or Collection Period, an amount equal to the product of (a)&nbsp;the Investor
Percentage for the related Collection Period, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;the Principal Collections for that Deposit Date or Collection Period,
as applicable.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Manufacturer
Overconcentration</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the sum of:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            excess, if any, of (i)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of Receivables that relate to
                                            a particular Manufacturer (other than Ford or one of its associated Manufacturers) with a
                                            long-term unsecured rating of &quot;A-&quot; or better by Standard&nbsp;&amp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 100%; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt">
<TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Poor's
and Fitch (if rated by Fitch), and &quot;A3&quot; or better by Moody's (if rated by Moody's) on the last day of the related Collection
Period, <U>over</U> (ii)&nbsp;__% of the Pool Balance on the last day of that Collection Period (or a higher percentage if the Rating
Agency Condition has been satisfied); plus</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            excess, if any, of (i)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of Receivables that relate to
                                            a particular Manufacturer (other than Ford or one of its associated Manufacturers) with a
                                            long-term unsecured rating of &quot;BBB+&quot; or lower by Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor's or
                                            unrated by Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor's, or &quot;BBB+&quot; or lower by Fitch (if rated by
                                            Fitch), or &quot;Baa1&quot; or lower by Moody's (if rated by Moody's) on the last day of
                                            the related Collection Period, <U>over</U> (ii)&nbsp;__% of the Pool Balance on the last
                                            day of that Collection Period (or a higher percentage if the Rating Agency Condition has
                                            been satisfied).</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Medium
and Heavy Truck Overconcentration</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the excess, if any, of (a)&nbsp;the aggregate principal
amount of Receivables that are Medium and Heavy Truck Receivables on the last day of the related Collection Period, <U>over</U> (b)&nbsp;__%
of the Pool Balance on the last day of that Collection Period (or a higher percentage if the Rating Agency Condition has been satisfied).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Back-up Servicing Fee</U>&quot; means, for any Payment Date, an amount equal to one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;the Back-up Servicing
Fee Rate, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;the percentage equivalent of a fraction with a numerator equal to the Floating Investor Percentage for
the related Collection Period and a denominator equal to the sum of the &quot;Floating Investor Percentages&quot; for all Series&nbsp;for
that Collection Period, <U>times</U> (c)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of Receivables on the last day of the prior Collection Period.
If no Back-up Servicing Agreement is in effect, all references to the Monthly Back-up Servicing Fee in this Indenture Supplement will
be considered to be deleted from this Indenture Supplement and have no further effect.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Depositor Servicing Fee</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;the product of
(i)&nbsp;the sum of the Servicing Fee Rate and the Back-up Servicing Fee Rate, <U>times</U> (ii)&nbsp;100% <U>minus</U> the sum of the
 &quot;Floating Investor Percentages&quot; for all Series&nbsp;for the related Collection Period, <U>times</U> (iii)&nbsp;the aggregate
principal amount of Receivables on the last day of the prior Collection Period, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;the percentage equivalent of a
fraction, the numerator of which is the Floating Investor Percentage for the related Collection Period and the denominator of which is
the sum of the &quot;Floating Investor Percentages&quot; for all Series&nbsp;for that Collection Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Investor Report</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;3.1(a)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Principal Amount</U>&quot; means, for each Payment Date, starting with the Payment Date in the month following the month in which [(a)&nbsp;the
Controlled Accumulation Period starts, a amount equal to the lesser of (i)&nbsp;the Controlled Deposit Amount for that Payment Date,
and (ii)&nbsp;the Adjusted Invested Amount of that Payment Date, or (b)] the Required Amortization Period or the Early Amortization Period
starts, the Adjusted Invested Amount on that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left"><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; width: 34%">AA-<!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->12<!-- Field: /Sequence --></TD><TD STYLE="width: 33%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Principal Payment Rate</U>&quot; means, for a Collection Period, the percentage equivalent of a fraction with (a)&nbsp;a numerator equal
to the Principal Collections for that Collection Period and (b)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the Pool Balance on the first day of that
Collection Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Monthly
Servicing Fee</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date, an amount equal to one-twelfth of the product of (a)&nbsp;the Servicing Fee Rate,
<U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;the percentage equivalent of a fraction with a numerator equal to the Floating Investor Percentage for the related
Collection Period and a denominator equal to the sum of the &quot;Floating Investor Percentages&quot; for all Series&nbsp;for that Collection
Period, <U>times</U> (c)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount of Receivables on the last day of the prior Collection Period, or for the
first Collection Period, the aggregate principal amount of Receivables on the Series&nbsp;Cutoff Date.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Non-Conforming
Receivable Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Determination Date, the excess, if any, of:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            sum, without duplication, of (i)&nbsp;the principal amount of Receivables that are Ineligible
                                            Receivables for that Determination Date, plus (ii)&nbsp;the aggregate amount of Dealer Overconcentrations,
                                            Development Dealer Overconcentrations, Fleet Overconcentrations, Manufacturer Overconcentrations,
                                            Medium and Heavy Truck Overconcentrations and Used Vehicle Overconcentrations for that Determination
                                            Date; <U>over</U></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            sum, without duplication, of (i)&nbsp;the principal amount of Receivables that are Ineligible
                                            Receivables that became Defaulted Receivables during the period from the prior Determination
                                            Date to the current Determination Date, <U>plus</U> (ii)&nbsp;the aggregate principal amount
                                            of Receivables contributing to Dealer Overconcentrations, Development Dealer Overconcentrations,
                                            Fleet Overconcentrations, Manufacturer Overconcentrations, Medium and Heavy Truck Overconcentrations
                                            and Used Vehicle Overconcentrations that, in each case, became Defaulted Receivables during
                                            the period from the prior Determination Date (or, in the case of the first Determination
                                            Date, the Series&nbsp;Cutoff Date) to the current Determination Date.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Note
Interest Rate</U>&quot; means, for each Class, the interest rate per annum stated in Section&nbsp;2.2(b)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement,
except that the interest rate for any Floating Rate Notes will not be less than 0.00%.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Note
Interest Shortfall</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date, an amount equal to the excess, if any, of the Accrued Note Interest
for the prior Payment Date for the Class&nbsp;<U>over</U> the amount of interest that was paid to the Noteholders of that Class&nbsp;on
the prior Payment Date, together with interest on the excess amount, to the extent lawful, at the Note Interest Rate for the Class&nbsp;for
that Interest Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Note
Monthly Interest</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date, the aggregate amount of interest accrued on the Note Balance of
that Class&nbsp;at the Note Interest Rate for that Class&nbsp;for the related Interest Period.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Redemption Period</U>&quot; means the period beginning with the ________ Payment Date before the Expected Final Payment Date.</FONT></P>

Redemption Price</U>&quot; means, for the Redemption Date, an amount equal to the sum of:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
Note Balance as of the Redemption Date; plus</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
Accrued Note Interest payable on the Redemption Date; plus</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;the
Accrued Step-Up Amounts payable on the Redemption Date; plus</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(d)&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;&#8239;any
accrued but unpaid Make-Whole Payments payable on the Redemption Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Note
Transfer</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;5.3(b)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Permanent
Regulation S Global Note</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;2.2(e)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Principal
Sharing Group One</U>&quot; means Series&nbsp;20__-__ and each other Series&nbsp;stated in the related Indenture Supplement to be included
in Principal Sharing Group One.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Principal
Shortfall</U>&quot; means, for Series&nbsp;20__-__ and a Payment Date, an amount equal to (a)&nbsp;for any Payment Date in the Revolving
Period, zero, and (b)&nbsp;for any Payment Date for the [Controlled Accumulation Period,] Required Amortization Period or Early Amortization
Period, the excess, if any, of the Monthly Principal Amount for that Payment Date, <U>over</U> the amount of Available Investor Principal
Collections for that Payment Date (excluding any Available Investor Principal Collections attributable to Shared Principal Collections).</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>QIB</U>&quot;
has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;5.3(c)(ii)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Rating
Agency</U>&quot; means each of _________ and __________.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Rating
Agency Condition</U>&quot; means, for an action or request and a Rating Agency, the satisfaction of either of the following conditions,
according to the then-current policies of the Rating Agency for that action or request:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            Rating Agency has notified the Depositors the Servicer, the Issuer and the Indenture Trustee
                                            in writing that the proposed action or request will not result in a downgrade or withdrawal
                                            of its then current rating on any of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes; or</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            Issuer has given ten Business Days' prior notice to the Rating Agency and the Rating Agency
                                            has not notified the Depositors, the Servicer, the Issuer and the Indenture Trustee before
                                            the end of the ten-day period that the action will result in a downgrade or withdrawal of
                                            its then current rating on any of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Collection Periods before the date of the calculation.]</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">

                                            amount in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account on that Payment Date
                                            (excluding any net investment earnings and before giving effect to any deposits or withdrawals
                                            made or to be made on that Payment Date); and</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Required Amount.]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Account Deposit Amount</U>&quot; means, for each Payment Date starting on the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation
Period Reserve Account Funding Date and until termination of the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account under Section&nbsp;4.7(c)(iii)&nbsp;of
the Indenture Supplement, the excess of (a)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Required Amount, <U>over
</U>(b)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Available Amount for that Payment Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Account Funding Date</U>&quot; means the Payment Date occurring in the second Collection Period before the
scheduled start of the Controlled Accumulation Period (or an earlier or later date as may be directed by the Servicer; <U>provided</U>
that, if the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Funding Date occurs on a later date, the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation
Period Reserve Account is expected to be fully funded by the start of the Controlled Accumulation Period).]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Account Required Amount</U>&quot; means an amount equal to ___ % of the initial Note Balance of the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accumulation Period Reserve Draw Amount</U>&quot; means, for a Payment Date relating to the Controlled Accumulation Period or the first
Payment Date in the Early Amortization Period, the lesser of (a)&nbsp;the excess, if any, of (i)&nbsp;an amount equal to one-twelfth
of the product of (A)&nbsp;the amount in the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Principal Funding Account on the prior Payment Date (excluding net investment
earnings), <U>times</U> (B)&nbsp;the weighted average (weighted by the aggregate Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__
Notes) of the Note Interest Rate for each Class&nbsp;of Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes for the related Interest Period, <U>over</U> (ii)&nbsp;the
portion of the Available Investor Interest Collections for that Payment Date that is net investment earnings from the Series&nbsp;20__-__
Accounts, and (b)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Accumulation Period Reserve Account Available Amount for that Payment Date.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

net investment earnings) on that date, <U>times</U> (b)&nbsp;a fraction with (i)&nbsp;a numerator equal to the Adjusted Invested Amount
as of that date and (ii)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the sum of the &quot;Adjusted Invested Amounts&quot; of all Series.</FONT></P>

and (b)&nbsp;the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve Account Required Amount for that Payment Date.</FONT></P>

the Closing Date is $__________.</FONT></P>

or (c)&nbsp;for a Payment Date in the Early Amortization Period on which the</FONT></P>

                                            the rate does not appear on the Federal Reserve Bank of New York's Website, the rate that

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Step-Up
Amounts</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date following the Expected Final Payment Date, the aggregate amount accrued
on the Note Balance of each Class&nbsp;of the Notes at the Step-Up Rate for that Interest Period.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Step-Up
Percentage</U>&quot; means the excess of the Subordinated Percentage calculated using a Subordination Factor of ___% <U>over</U> the
Subordinated Percentage calculated using a Subordination Factor of ___%.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Step-Up
Rate</U>&quot; means, (a)&nbsp;for each Class&nbsp;of Notes other than the Floating Rate Notes, a rate equal to the Note Interest Rate
for that Class&nbsp;minus ___% and (b)&nbsp;for the Floating Rate Notes, a rate equal to the portion of the Note Interest Rate in excess
of the Benchmark for that Class.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">[&quot;<U>Step-Up
Shortfall</U>&quot; means, for a Class&nbsp;and a Payment Date after the Expected Final Payment Date:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(a)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">any
                                            Step-Up Amounts for a Class&nbsp;for the prior Payment Date; <U>plus</U></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(b)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">any
                                            Step-Up Shortfall for a Class&nbsp;for the prior Payment Date; <U>minus</U></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">(c)</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">the
                                            amount of the Accrued Step-Up Amounts paid to the Noteholders on the prior Payment Date.]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Subordinated
Percentage</U>&quot; means the sum of (a)&nbsp;the percentage equivalent of a fraction with (i)&nbsp;a numerator equal to the Subordination
Factor and (ii)&nbsp;a denominator equal to the excess of 100%, <U>over</U> the Subordination Factor, <U>plus</U> (b)&nbsp;the Supplemental
Subordinated Percentage, if any, established by the Issuer at the direction of the Depositors according to Section&nbsp;2.5 of the Indenture
Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Subordination
Factor</U>&quot; means, for the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Notes, (a)&nbsp;for a Determination Date not stated in clause (b), ___% or (b)&nbsp;for
a Determination Date during a Subordination Step-Up Period, unless the Depositors have elected to increase the Series&nbsp;20__-__ Reserve
Account Required Percentage according to Section&nbsp;4.9(b)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement, ___%.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Subordination
Step-Up Period</U>&quot; means any period starting on the Determination Date for which the average of the Monthly Principal Payment Rates
for the three prior Collection Periods is less than ___% and ending on the Determination Date for which the average of the Monthly Principal
Payment Rates for the three prior Collection Periods is equal to or greater than ___%.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&quot;<U>Supplemental
Subordinated Percentage</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;2.5 of the Indenture Supplement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Regulation S Global Note</U>&quot; has the meaning stated in Section&nbsp;2.2(e)&nbsp;of the Indenture Supplement.]</FONT></P>

Benchmark Replacement</U>&quot; means the Benchmark Replacement excluding the Benchmark Replacement Adjustment.]</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Reference
is made to the terms of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note stated on the reverse of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, which will
have the same effect as though fully stated on the face of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">Unless
the certificate of authentication on this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note has been executed by or on behalf of the Indenture Trustee,
by manual signature, this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note will not be entitled to any benefit under the Indenture or the Indenture Supplement
referred to on the reverse of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, or be valid for any purpose.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></P>

to all of the terms of the Series&nbsp;Agreement. All terms used in this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note that are defined in the Series&nbsp;Agreement
have the meanings stated in the Series&nbsp;Agreement. In the event of any conflict or inconsistency between the Series&nbsp;Agreement
and this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, the Series&nbsp;Agreement controls.</FONT></P>

will be made (a)&nbsp;(i)&nbsp;if the Noteholder has given the Note Registrar appropriate instructions at least five Business Days before
that Payment Date and the aggregate original principal amount of the Noteholder's Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Notes is at least $1,000,000,
by wire transfer to the account of the Noteholder or (ii)&nbsp;by check mailed first class, postage prepaid to each Noteholder (at the
Noteholder's address as it appears in the Note Register), except that for any Notes registered in the name of the nominee of the Clearing
Agency, the distribution will be made by wire transfer and (b)&nbsp;without presentation or surrender of any Note or the making of any
notation on the Note. Final payment of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note will be made only on presentation and surrender of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D]

in connection with the exchange.</FONT></P>

be affected by notice to the contrary.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">The
holder of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, by its acceptance of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, and the owner of an interest
or participation in this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, by its acceptance of an interest or participation, covenant and agree that (a)&nbsp;they
will not at any time start or pursue against the Issuer or the Depositors, or join in starting or pursuing against the Issuer or the
Depositors, any bankruptcy, reorganization, arrangement, insolvency or liquidation proceedings, or other proceedings under any United
States federal or state bankruptcy or similar law in connection with any obligations relating to the Notes, the Indenture, the Indenture
Supplement or any of the other related transaction documents and (b)&nbsp;if any Depositor becomes a debtor or debtor in possession in
a case under any applicable United States federal or state bankruptcy, insolvency or other similar law now or later in effect or subject
to any insolvency, reorganization, liquidation, rehabilitation or other similar proceedings, any claim that the holders of the Notes
of any Series&nbsp;may have at any time against the Issuer's assets allocated according to the Indenture to any Series&nbsp;unrelated
to the Notes, and any claim that the holders of the Notes have at any time against the Depositors that they may seek to enforce against
the Issuer's assets allocated to any unrelated Series, will be subordinate to the payment in full (including post-petition interest)
of the claims of the holders of any Notes of the unrelated Series&nbsp;and of the holders of any other notes, bonds, contracts or other
obligations relating to the unrelated Series.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">The
holder of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, by acceptance of this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, and each holder of an interest or
participation in this Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Note, agree to treat the Class&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] Notes as indebtedness of the Issuer
for applicable United States federal, state and local income and franchise tax purposes.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 12pt"><B>THIS
CLASS&nbsp;[A[-__]/B/C/D] NOTE WILL BE GOVERNED BY AND CONSTRUED ACCORDING TO THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK.</B></FONT></P>
